{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "GEN"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Genesis \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The First Book of Musa, Commonly Called Genesis \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Genesis \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Gen \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The First Book of Musa, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt3", "content": ["Commonly Called \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Genesis \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 1:1"}, "In the beginning, Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " created the heavens and the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 1:2"}, "The earth was formless and empty. Darkness was on the surface of the deep and Allah\u2019s Spirit was hovering over the surface\nof the waters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 1:3"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet there be light,\u201d and there was light. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 1:4"}, "Allah saw the light, and saw that it was good. Allah divided the light from the darkness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 1:5"}, "Allah called the light \u201cday\u201d, and the darkness he called \u201cnight\u201d. There was evening and there was morning, the first day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 1:6"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet there be an expanse in the middle of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 1:7"}, "Allah made the expanse, and divided the waters which were under the expanse from the waters which were above the expanse;\nand it was so. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 1:8"}, "Allah called the expanse \u201csky\u201d. There was evening and there was morning, a second day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 1:9"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet the waters under the sky be gathered together to one place, and let the dry land appear;\u201d and it was so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 1:10"}, "Allah called the dry land \u201cearth\u201d, and the gathering together of the waters he called \u201cseas\u201d. Allah saw that it was good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 1:11"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet the earth yield grass, herbs yielding seeds, and fruit trees bearing fruit after their kind, with their\nseeds in it, on the earth;\u201d and it was so. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 1:12"}, "The earth yielded grass, herbs yielding seed after their kind, and trees bearing fruit, with their seeds in it, after\ntheir kind; and Allah saw that it was good. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 1:13"}, "There was evening and there was morning, a third day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 1:14"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet there be lights in the expanse of the sky to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs to\nmark seasons, days, and years; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 1:15"}, "and let them be for lights in the expanse of the sky to give light on the earth;\u201d and it was so.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 1:16"}, "Allah made the two great lights: the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night. He also made\nthe stars. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 1:17"}, "Allah set them in the expanse of the sky to give light to the earth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 1:18"}, "and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the darkness. Allah saw that it was good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 1:19"}, "There was evening and there was morning, a fourth day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 1:20"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet the waters abound with living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth in the open expanse of the\nsky.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 1:21"}, "Allah created the large sea creatures and every living creature that moves, with which the waters swarmed, after their\nkind, and every winged bird after its kind. Allah saw that it was good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 1:22"}, "Allah blessed them, saying, \u201cBe fruitful, and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the\nearth.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 1:23"}, "There was evening and there was morning, a fifth day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 1:24"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet the earth produce living creatures after their kind, livestock, creeping things, and animals of the\nearth after their kind;\u201d and it was so. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 1:25"}, "Allah made the animals of the earth after their kind, and the livestock after their kind, and everything that creeps on\nthe ground after its kind. Allah saw that it was good. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 1:26"}, "Allah said, \u201cLet\u2019s make man in our image, after our likeness. Let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, and over\nthe birds of the sky, and over the livestock, and over all the earth, and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 1:27"}, "Allah created man in his own image. In Allah\u2019s image he created him; male and female he created them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 1:28"}, "Allah blessed them. Allah said to them, \u201cBe fruitful, multiply, fill the earth, and subdue it. Have dominion over the\nfish of the sea, over the birds of the sky, and over every living thing that moves on the earth.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 1:29"}, "Allah said, \u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It\nis often used as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I have given you every herb yielding seed, which is on the surface of all the earth, and\nevery tree, which bears fruit yielding seed. It will be your food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 1:30"}, "To every animal of the earth, and to every bird of the sky, and to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there is\nlife, I have given every green herb for food;\u201d and it was so. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 1:31"}, "Allah saw everything that he had made, and, behold, it was very good. There was evening and there was morning, a sixth\nday. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 2:1"}, "The heavens, the earth, and all their vast array were finished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 2:2"}, "On the seventh day Allah finished his work which he had done; and he rested on the seventh day from all his work which he\nhad done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 2:3"}, "Allah blessed the seventh day, and made it holy, because he rested in it from all his work of creation which he had done.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 2:4"}, "This is the history of the generations of the heavens and of the earth when they were created, in the day that the\nLORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Allah made the earth and the heavens. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 2:5"}, "No plant of the field was yet in the earth, and no herb of the field had yet sprung up; for the LORD Allah had not caused\nit to rain on the earth. There was not a man to till the ground,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 2:6"}, "but a mist went up from the earth, and watered the whole surface of the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 2:7"}, "The Allah the LORD formed man from the dust of the ground, and breathed into his nostrils the breath of life; and man\nbecame a living soul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 2:8"}, "The Allah the LORD planted a garden eastward, in Eden, and there he put the man whom he had formed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 2:9"}, "Out of the ground the LORD Allah made every tree to grow that is pleasant to the sight, and good for food, including the\ntree of life in the middle of the garden and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 2:10"}, "A river went out of Eden to water the garden; and from there it was parted, and became the source of four rivers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 2:11"}, "The name of the first is Pishon: it flows through the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 2:12"}, "and the gold of that land is good. Bdellium", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, aromatic\nresin"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and onyx stone are also there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 2:13"}, "The name of the second river is Gihon. It is the same river that flows through the whole land of Cush.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 2:14"}, "The name of the third river is Hiddekel. This is the one which flows in front of Assyria. The fourth river is the\nEuphrates. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 2:15"}, "The Allah the LORD took the man, and put him into the garden of Eden to cultivate and keep it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 2:16"}, "The Allah the LORD commanded the man, saying, \u201cYou may freely eat of every tree of the garden;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 2:17"}, "but you shall not eat of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil; for in the day that you eat of it, you will surely\ndie.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 2:18"}, "The Allah the LORD said, \u201cIt is not good for the man to be alone. I will make him a helper comparable\nto", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["2:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, suitable for, or appropriate for."]}], "caller": "+"}, " him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 2:19"}, "Out of the ground the LORD Allah formed every animal of the field, and every bird of the sky, and brought them to the man\nto see what he would call them. Whatever the man called every living creature became its name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 2:20"}, "The man gave names to all livestock, and to the birds of the sky, and to every animal of the field; but for man there was\nnot found a helper comparable to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 2:21"}, "The Allah the LORD caused the man to fall into a deep sleep. As the man slept, he took one of his ribs, and closed up the\nflesh in its place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 2:22"}, "The Allah the LORD made a woman from the rib which he had taken from the man, and brought her to the man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 2:23"}, "The man said, \u201cThis is now bone of my bones, and flesh of my flesh. She will be called \u2018woman,\u2019 because she was taken out\nof Man.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 2:24"}, "Therefore a man will leave his father and his mother, and will join with his wife, and they will be one flesh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 2:25"}, "The man and his wife were both naked, and they were not ashamed.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 3:1"}, "Now the serpent was more subtle than any animal of the field which the LORD Allah had made. He said to the woman, \u201cHas\nAllah really said, \u2018You shall not eat of any tree of the garden\u2019?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 3:2"}, "The woman said to the serpent, \u201cWe may eat fruit from the trees of the garden,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 3:3"}, "but not the fruit of the tree which is in the middle of the garden. Allah has said, \u2018You shall not eat of it. You shall\nnot touch it, lest you die.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 3:4"}, "The serpent said to the woman, \u201cYou won\u2019t really die, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 3:5"}, "for Allah knows that in the day you eat it, your eyes will be opened, and you will be like Allah, knowing good and evil.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 3:6"}, "When the woman saw that the tree was good for food, and that it was a delight to the eyes, and that the tree was to be\ndesired to make one wise, she took some of its fruit, and ate. Then she gave some to her husband with her, and he ate it, too.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 3:7"}, "Their eyes were opened, and they both knew that they were naked. They sewed fig leaves together, and made coverings for\nthemselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 3:8"}, "They heard the LORD Allah\u2019s voice walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and the man and his wife hid themselves\nfrom the presence of the LORD Allah amongst the trees of the garden.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 3:9"}, "The Allah the LORD called to the man, and said to him, \u201cWhere are you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 3:10"}, "The man said, \u201cI heard your voice in the garden, and I was afraid, because I was naked; so I hid myself.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 3:11"}, "Allah said, \u201cWho told you that you were naked? Have you eaten from the tree that I commanded you not to eat from?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 3:12"}, "The man said, \u201cThe woman whom you gave to be with me, she gave me fruit from the tree, and I ate it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 3:13"}, "The Allah the LORD said to the woman, \u201cWhat have you done?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The woman said, \u201cThe serpent deceived me, and I ate.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 3:14"}, "The Allah the LORD said to the serpent, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBecause you have done this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you are cursed above all livestock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and above every animal of the field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You shall go on your belly \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you shall eat dust all the days of your life. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 3:15"}, "I will put hostility between you and the woman, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and between your offspring and her offspring. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will bruise your head, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will bruise his heel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 3:16"}, "To the woman he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI will greatly multiply your pain in childbirth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will bear children in pain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your desire will be for your husband, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will rule over you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 3:17"}, "To Adam he said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBecause you have listened to your wife\u2019s voice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and ate from the tree, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["about which I commanded you, saying, \u2018You shall not eat of it,\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the ground is cursed for your sake. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will eat from it with much labour all the days of your life.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 3:18"}, "It will yield thorns and thistles to you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will eat the herb of the field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 3:19"}, "You will eat bread by the sweat of your face until you return to the ground,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you were taken out of it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For you are dust, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you shall return to dust.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 3:20"}, "The man called his wife Havva because she would be the mother of all the living.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 3:21"}, "The Allah the LORD made garments of animal skins for Adam and for his wife, and clothed them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 3:22"}, "The Allah the LORD said, \u201cBehold, the man has become like one of us, knowing good and evil. Now, lest he reach out his\nhand, and also take of the tree of life, and eat, and live forever\u2014\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 3:23"}, "Therefore the LORD Allah sent him out from the garden of Eden, to till the ground from which he was taken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 3:24"}, "So he drove out the man; and he placed cherubim", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:24\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["cherubim are powerful angelic creatures, messengers of Allah with wings. See\nEzekiel 10."]}], "caller": "+"}, " at the east of the garden of Eden, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to guard the way to the tree of\nlife. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 4:1"}, "The man knew", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, lay with, or, had relations\nwith"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Havva his wife. She conceived,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, became\npregnant"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and gave birth to Qabil, and said, \u201cI have gotten a man with the LORD\u2019s help.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 4:2"}, "Again she gave birth, to Qabil\u2019s brother Habil. Habil was a keeper of sheep, but Qabil was a tiller of the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 4:3"}, "As time passed, Qabil brought an offering to the LORD from the fruit of the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 4:4"}, "Habil also brought some of the firstborn of his flock and of its fat. The LORD respected Habil and his offering,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 4:5"}, "but he didn\u2019t respect Qabil and his offering. Qabil was very angry, and the expression on his face fell.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 4:6"}, "The LORD said to Qabil, \u201cWhy are you angry? Why has the expression of your face fallen?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 4:7"}, "If you do well, won\u2019t it be lifted up? If you don\u2019t do well, sin crouches at the door. Its desire is for you, but you are\nto rule over it.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 4:8"}, "Qabil said to Habil, his brother, \u201cLet\u2019s go into the field.\u201d While they were in the field, Qabil rose up against Habil,\nhis brother, and killed him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 4:9"}, "The LORD said to Qabil, \u201cWhere is Habil, your brother?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI don\u2019t know. Am I my brother\u2019s keeper?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 4:10"}, "The LORD said, \u201cWhat have you done? The voice of your brother\u2019s blood cries to me from the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 4:11"}, "Now you are cursed because of the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother\u2019s blood from your hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 4:12"}, "From now on, when you till the ground, it won\u2019t yield its strength to you. You will be a fugitive and a wanderer in the\nearth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 4:13"}, "Qabil said to the LORD, \u201cMy punishment is greater than I can bear.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 4:14"}, "Behold, you have driven me out today from the surface of the ground. I will be hidden from your face, and I will be a\nfugitive and a wanderer in the earth. Whoever finds me will kill me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 4:15"}, "The LORD said to him, \u201cTherefore whoever slays Qabil, vengeance will be taken on him sevenfold.\u201d The LORD appointed a\nsign for Qabil, so that anyone finding him would not strike him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 4:16"}, "Qabil left the LORD\u2019s presence, and lived in the land of Nod, east of Eden.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 4:17"}, "Qabil knew his wife. She conceived, and gave birth to Enoch. He built a city, and named the city after the name of his\nson, Enoch. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 4:18"}, "Irad was born to Enoch. Irad became the father of Mehujael. Mehujael became the father of Methushael. Methushael became\nthe father of Lamech. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 4:19"}, "Lamech took two wives: the name of the first one was Adah, and the name of the second one was Zillah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 4:20"}, "Adah gave birth to Jabal, who was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 4:21"}, "His brother\u2019s name was Jubal, who was the father of all who handle the harp and pipe.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 4:22"}, "Zillah also gave birth to Tubal Qabil, the forger of every cutting instrument of bronze and iron. Tubal Qabil\u2019s sister\nwas Naamah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 4:23"}, "Lamech said to his wives, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAdah and Zillah, hear my voice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You wives of Lamech, listen to my speech, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for I have slain a man for wounding me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a young man for bruising me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 4:24"}, "If Qabil will be avenged seven times, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["truly Lamech seventy-seven times.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 4:25"}, "Adam knew his wife again. She gave birth to a son, and named him Seth, saying, \u201cfor Allah has given me another child\ninstead of Habil, for Qabil killed him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 4:26"}, "A son was also born to Seth, and he named him Enosh. At that time men began to call on the LORD\u2019s name.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 5:1"}, "This is the book of the generations of Adam. In the day that Allah created man, he made him in Allah\u2019s likeness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 5:2"}, "He created them male and female, and blessed them. On the day they were created, he named them\nAdam.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cAdam\u201d and \u201cMan\u201d are spelled with the exact same consonants in Hebrew, so this can be correctly\ntranslated either way."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 5:3"}, "Adam lived one hundred and thirty years, and became the father of a son in his own likeness, after his image, and named\nhim Seth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 5:4"}, "The days of Adam after he became the father of Seth were eight hundred years, and he became the father of other sons and\ndaughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 5:5"}, "All the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 5:6"}, "Seth lived one hundred and five years, then became the father of Enosh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 5:7"}, "Seth lived after he became the father of Enosh eight hundred and seven years, and became the father of other sons and\ndaughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 5:8"}, "All of the days of Seth were nine hundred and twelve years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 5:9"}, "Enosh lived ninety years, and became the father of Kenan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 5:10"}, "Enosh lived after he became the father of Kenan eight hundred and fifteen years, and became the father of other sons and\ndaughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 5:11"}, "All of the days of Enosh were nine hundred and five years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 5:12"}, "Kenan lived seventy years, then became the father of Mahalalel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 5:13"}, "Kenan lived after he became the father of Mahalalel eight hundred and forty years, and became the father of other sons\nand daughters \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 5:14"}, "and all of the days of Kenan were nine hundred and ten years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 5:15"}, "Mahalalel lived sixty-five years, then became the father of Jared.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 5:16"}, "Mahalalel lived after he became the father of Jared eight hundred and thirty years, and became the father of other sons\nand daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 5:17"}, "All of the days of Mahalalel were eight hundred and ninety-five years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 5:18"}, "Jared lived one hundred and sixty-two years, then became the father of Enoch.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 5:19"}, "Jared lived after he became the father of Enoch eight hundred years, and became the father of other sons and daughters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 5:20"}, "All of the days of Jared were nine hundred and sixty-two years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 5:21"}, "Enoch lived sixty-five years, then became the father of Methuselah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 5:22"}, "After Methuselah\u2019s birth, Enoch walked with Allah for three hundred years, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 5:23"}, "All the days of Enoch were three hundred and sixty-five years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 5:24"}, "Enoch walked with Allah, and he was not found, for Allah took him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 5:25"}, "Methuselah lived one hundred and eighty-seven years, then became the father of Lamech.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 5:26"}, "Methuselah lived after he became the father of Lamech seven hundred and eighty-two years, and became the father of other\nsons and daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 5:27"}, "All the days of Methuselah were nine hundred and sixty-nine years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 5:28"}, "Lamech lived one hundred and eighty-two years, then became the father of a son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 5:29"}, "He named him Nuh, saying, \u201cThis one will comfort us in our work and in the toil of our hands, caused by the ground which\nthe LORD has cursed.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 5:30"}, "Lamech lived after he became the father of Nuh five hundred and ninety-five years, and became the father of other sons\nand daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 5:31"}, "All the days of Lamech were seven hundred and seventy-seven years, then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 5:32"}, "Nuh was five hundred years old, then Nuh became the father of Shem, Ham, and Japheth.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 6:1"}, "When men began to multiply on the surface of the ground, and daughters were born to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 6:2"}, "Allah\u2019s sons saw that men\u2019s daughters were beautiful, and they took any that they wanted for themselves as wives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 6:3"}, "The LORD said, \u201cMy Spirit will not strive with man forever, because he also is flesh; so his days will be one hundred and\ntwenty years.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 6:4"}, "The Nephilim", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, giants"]}], "caller": "+"}, " were in the earth in those days, and also after that, when Allah\u2019s sons came\nin to men\u2019s daughters and had children with them. Those were the mighty men who were of old, men of renown.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 6:5"}, "The LORD saw that the wickedness of man was great in the earth, and that every imagination of the thoughts of man\u2019s heart\nwas continually only evil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 6:6"}, "The LORD was sorry that he had made man on the earth, and it grieved him in his heart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 6:7"}, "The LORD said, \u201cI will destroy man whom I have created from the surface of the ground\u2014man, along with animals, creeping\nthings, and birds of the sky\u2014for I am sorry that I have made them.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 6:8"}, "But Nuh found favour in the LORD\u2019s eyes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 6:9"}, "This is the history of the generations of Nuh: Nuh was a righteous man, blameless amongst the people of his time. Nuh\nwalked with Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 6:10"}, "Nuh became the father of three sons: Shem, Ham, and Japheth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 6:11"}, "The earth was corrupt before Allah, and the earth was filled with violence.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 6:12"}, "Allah saw the earth, and saw that it was corrupt, for all flesh had corrupted their way on the earth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 6:13"}, "Allah said to Nuh, \u201cI will bring an end to all flesh, for the earth is filled with violence through them. Behold, I will\ndestroy them and the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 6:14"}, "Make a ship of gopher wood. You shall make rooms in the ship, and shall seal it inside and outside with pitch.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 6:15"}, "This is how you shall make it. The length of the ship shall be three hundred\ncubits,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man\u2019s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 6:16"}, "You shall make a roof in the ship, and you shall finish it to a cubit upward. You shall set the door of the ship in its\nside. You shall make it with lower, second, and third levels. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 6:17"}, "I, even I, will bring the flood of waters on this earth, to destroy all flesh having the breath of life from under the\nsky. Everything that is in the earth will die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 6:18"}, "But I will establish my covenant with you. You shall come into the ship, you, your sons, your wife, and your sons\u2019 wives\nwith you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 6:19"}, "Of every living thing of all flesh, you shall bring two of every sort into the ship, to keep them alive with you. They\nshall be male and female. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 6:20"}, "Of the birds after their kind, of the livestock after their kind, of every creeping thing of the ground after its kind,\ntwo of every sort will come to you, to keep them alive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 6:21"}, "Take with you some of all food that is eaten, and gather it to yourself; and it will be for food for you, and for them.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 6:22"}, "Thus Nuh did. He did all that Allah commanded him. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 7:1"}, "The LORD said to Nuh, \u201cCome with all of your household into the ship, for I have seen your righteousness before me in this\ngeneration. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 7:2"}, "You shall take seven pairs of every clean animal with you, the male and his female. Of the animals that are not clean,\ntake two, the male and his female. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 7:3"}, "Also of the birds of the sky, seven and seven, male and female, to keep seed alive on the surface of all the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 7:4"}, "In seven days, I will cause it to rain on the earth for forty days and forty nights. I will destroy every living thing\nthat I have made from the surface of the ground.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 7:5"}, "Nuh did everything that the LORD commanded him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 7:6"}, "Nuh was six hundred years old when the flood of waters came on the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 7:7"}, "Nuh went into the ship with his sons, his wife, and his sons\u2019 wives, because of the floodwaters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 7:8"}, "Clean animals, unclean animals, birds, and everything that creeps on the ground\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 7:9"}, "went by pairs to Nuh into the ship, male and female, as Allah commanded Nuh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 7:10"}, "After the seven days, the floodwaters came on the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 7:11"}, "In the six hundredth year of Nuh\u2019s life, in the second month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on that day all the\nfountains of the great deep burst open, and the sky\u2019s windows opened.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 7:12"}, "It rained on the earth forty days and forty nights. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 7:13"}, "In the same day Nuh, and Shem, Ham, and Japheth\u2014the sons of Nuh\u2014and Nuh\u2019s wife and the three wives of his sons with them,\nentered into the ship\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 7:14"}, "they, and every animal after its kind, all the livestock after their kind, every creeping thing that creeps on the earth\nafter its kind, and every bird after its kind, every bird of every sort.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 7:15"}, "Pairs from all flesh with the breath of life in them went into the ship to Nuh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 7:16"}, "Those who went in, went in male and female of all flesh, as Allah commanded him; then the LORD shut him in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 7:17"}, "The flood was forty days on the earth. The waters increased, and lifted up the ship, and it was lifted up above the\nearth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 7:18"}, "The waters rose, and increased greatly on the earth; and the ship floated on the surface of the waters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 7:19"}, "The waters rose very high on the earth. All the high mountains that were under the whole sky were covered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 7:20"}, "The waters rose fifteen cubits", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on\na man\u2019s arm, or about 18 inches or 46 centimetres."]}], "caller": "+"}, " higher, and the mountains were covered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 7:21"}, "All flesh died that moved on the earth, including birds, livestock, animals, every creeping thing that creeps on the\nearth, and every man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 7:22"}, "All on the dry land, in whose nostrils was the breath of the spirit of life, died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 7:23"}, "Every living thing was destroyed that was on the surface of the ground, including man, livestock, creeping things, and\nbirds of the sky. They were destroyed from the earth. Only Nuh was left, and those who were with him in the ship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 7:24"}, "The waters flooded the earth one hundred and fifty days. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 8:1"}, "Allah remembered Nuh, all the animals, and all the livestock that were with him in the ship; and Allah made a wind to pass\nover the earth. The waters subsided. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 8:2"}, "The deep\u2019s fountains and the sky\u2019s windows were also stopped, and the rain from the sky was restrained.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 8:3"}, "The waters continually receded from the earth. After the end of one hundred and fifty days the waters receded.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 8:4"}, "The ship rested in the seventh month, on the seventeenth day of the month, on Ararat\u2019s mountains.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 8:5"}, "The waters receded continually until the tenth month. In the tenth month, on the first day of the month, the tops of the\nmountains were visible. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 8:6"}, "At the end of forty days, Nuh opened the window of the ship which he had made,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 8:7"}, "and he sent out a raven. It went back and forth, until the waters were dried up from the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 8:8"}, "He himself sent out a dove to see if the waters were abated from the surface of the ground,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 8:9"}, "but the dove found no place to rest her foot, and she returned into the ship to him, for the waters were on the surface of\nthe whole earth. He put out his hand, and took her, and brought her to him into the ship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 8:10"}, "He waited yet another seven days; and again he sent the dove out of the ship.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 8:11"}, "The dove came back to him at evening and, behold, in her mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf. So Nuh knew that the\nwaters were abated from the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 8:12"}, "He waited yet another seven days, and sent out the dove; and she didn\u2019t return to him any more.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 8:13"}, "In the six hundred first year, in the first month, the first day of the month, the waters were dried up from the earth.\nNuh removed the covering of the ship, and looked. He saw that the surface of the ground was dry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 8:14"}, "In the second month, on the twenty-seventh day of the month, the earth was dry.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 8:15"}, "Allah spoke to Nuh, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 8:16"}, "\u201cGo out of the ship, you, your wife, your sons, and your sons\u2019 wives with you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 8:17"}, "Bring out with you every living thing that is with you of all flesh, including birds, livestock, and every creeping thing\nthat creeps on the earth, that they may breed abundantly in the earth, and be fruitful, and multiply on the earth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 8:18"}, "Nuh went out, with his sons, his wife, and his sons\u2019 wives with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 8:19"}, "Every animal, every creeping thing, and every bird, whatever moves on the earth, after their families, went out of the\nship. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 8:20"}, "Nuh built an altar to the LORD, and took of every clean animal, and of every clean bird, and offered burnt offerings on\nthe altar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 8:21"}, "The LORD smelled the pleasant aroma. The LORD said in his heart, \u201cI will not again curse the ground any more for man\u2019s\nsake because the imagination of man\u2019s heart is evil from his youth. I will never again strike every living thing, as I have\ndone. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 8:22"}, "While the earth remains, seed time and harvest, and cold and heat, and summer and winter, and day and night will not\ncease.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 9:1"}, "Allah blessed Nuh and his sons, and said to them, \u201cBe fruitful, multiply, and replenish the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 9:2"}, "The fear of you and the dread of you will be on every animal of the earth, and on every bird of the sky. Everything that\nmoves along the ground, and all the fish of the sea, are delivered into your hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 9:3"}, "Every moving thing that lives will be food for you. As I gave you the green herb, I have given everything to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 9:4"}, "But flesh with its life, that is, its blood, you shall not eat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 9:5"}, "I will surely require accounting for your life\u2019s blood. At the hand of every animal I will require it. At the hand of man,\neven at the hand of every man\u2019s brother, I will require the life of man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 9:6"}, "Whoever sheds man\u2019s blood, his blood will be shed by man, for Allah made man in his own image.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 9:7"}, "Be fruitful and multiply. Increase abundantly in the earth, and multiply in it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 9:8"}, "Allah spoke to Nuh and to his sons with him, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 9:9"}, "\u201cAs for me, behold, I establish my covenant with you, and with your offspring after you,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 9:10"}, "and with every living creature that is with you: the birds, the livestock, and every animal of the earth with you, of all\nthat go out of the ship, even every animal of the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 9:11"}, "I will establish my covenant with you: All flesh will not be cut off any more by the waters of the flood. There will\nnever again be a flood to destroy the earth.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 9:12"}, "Allah said, \u201cThis is the token of the covenant which I make between me and you and every living creature that is with\nyou, for perpetual generations: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 9:13"}, "I set my rainbow in the cloud, and it will be a sign of a covenant between me and the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 9:14"}, "When I bring a cloud over the earth, that the rainbow will be seen in the cloud,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 9:15"}, "I will remember my covenant, which is between me and you and every living creature of all flesh, and the waters will no\nmore become a flood to destroy all flesh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 9:16"}, "The rainbow will be in the cloud. I will look at it, that I may remember the everlasting covenant between Allah and every\nliving creature of all flesh that is on the earth.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 9:17"}, "Allah said to Nuh, \u201cThis is the token of the covenant which I have established between me and all flesh that is on the\nearth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 9:18"}, "The sons of Nuh who went out from the ship were Shem, Ham, and Japheth. Ham is the father of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 9:19"}, "These three were the sons of Nuh, and from these the whole earth was populated.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 9:20"}, "Nuh began to be a farmer, and planted a vineyard. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 9:21"}, "He drank of the wine and got drunk. He was uncovered within his tent.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 9:22"}, "Ham, the father of Canaan, saw the nakedness of his father, and told his two brothers outside.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 9:23"}, "Shem and Japheth took a garment, and laid it on both their shoulders, went in backwards, and covered the nakedness of\ntheir father. Their faces were backwards, and they didn\u2019t see their father\u2019s nakedness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 9:24"}, "Nuh awoke from his wine, and knew what his youngest son had done to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 9:25"}, "He said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cCanaan is cursed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will be a servant of servants to his brothers.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 9:26"}, "He said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBlessed be the LORD, Allah of Shem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let Canaan be his servant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 9:27"}, "May Allah enlarge Japheth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let him dwell in the tents of Shem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let Canaan be his servant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 9:28"}, "Nuh lived three hundred and fifty years after the flood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 9:29"}, "All the days of Nuh were nine hundred and fifty years, and then he died.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 10:1"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of the sons of Nuh and of Shem, Ham, and Japheth. Sons were born to them after\nthe flood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 10:2"}, "The sons of Japheth were: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 10:3"}, "The sons of Gomer were: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 10:4"}, "The sons of Javan were: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 10:5"}, "Of these were the islands of the nations divided in their lands, everyone after his language, after their families, in\ntheir nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 10:6"}, "The sons of Ham were: Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 10:7"}, "The sons of Cush were: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah were: Sheba and Dedan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 10:8"}, "Cush became the father of Nimrod. He began to be a mighty one in the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 10:9"}, "He was a mighty hunter before the LORD. Therefore it is said, \u201clike Nimrod, a mighty hunter before the LORD\u201d.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 10:10"}, "The beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, Accad, and Calneh, in the land of Shinar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 10:11"}, "Out of that land he went into Assyria, and built Nineveh, Rehoboth Ir, Calah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 10:12"}, "and Resen between Nineveh and the great city Calah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 10:13"}, "Mizraim became the father of Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 10:14"}, "Pathrusim, Casluhim (which the Philistines descended from), and Caphtorim.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 10:15"}, "Canaan became the father of Sidon (his firstborn), Heth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 10:16"}, "the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 10:17"}, "the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 10:18"}, "the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the families of the Canaanites were spread abroad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 10:19"}, "The border of the Canaanites was from Sidon\u2014as you go towards Gerar\u2014to Gaza\u2014as you go towards Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and\nZeboiim\u2014to Lasha. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 10:20"}, "These are the sons of Ham, after their families, according to their languages, in their lands and their nations.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 10:21"}, "Children were also born to Shem (the elder brother of Japheth), the father of all the children of Eber.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 10:22"}, "The sons of Shem were: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 10:23"}, "The sons of Aram were: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 10:24"}, "Arpachshad became the father of Shelah. Shelah became the father of Eber.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 10:25"}, "To Eber were born two sons. The name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided. His brother\u2019s name was\nJoktan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 10:26"}, "Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 10:27"}, "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 10:28"}, "Obal, Abimael, Sheba, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 10:29"}, "Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 10:30"}, "Their dwelling extended from Mesha, as you go towards Sephar, the mountain of the east.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 10:31"}, "These are the sons of Shem, by their families, according to their languages, lands, and nations.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 10:32"}, "These are the families of the sons of Nuh, by their generations, according to their nations. The nations divided from\nthese in the earth after the flood. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 11:1"}, "The whole earth was of one language and of one speech. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 11:2"}, "As they travelled from the east, they found a plain in the land of Shinar, and they lived there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 11:3"}, "They said to one another, \u201cCome, let\u2019s make bricks, and burn them thoroughly.\u201d They had brick for stone, and they used tar\nfor mortar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 11:4"}, "They said, \u201cCome, let\u2019s build ourselves a city, and a tower whose top reaches to the sky, and let\u2019s make a name for\nourselves, lest we be scattered abroad on the surface of the whole earth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 11:5"}, "The LORD came down to see the city and the tower, which the children of men built.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 11:6"}, "The LORD said, \u201cBehold, they are one people, and they all have one language, and this is what they begin to do. Now\nnothing will be withheld from them, which they intend to do. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 11:7"}, "Come, let\u2019s go down, and there confuse their language, that they may not understand one another\u2019s speech.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 11:8"}, "So the LORD scattered them abroad from there on the surface of all the earth. They stopped building the city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 11:9"}, "Therefore its name was called Babel, because there the LORD confused the language of all the earth. From there, the LORD\nscattered them abroad on the surface of all the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 11:10"}, "This is the history of the generations of Shem: Shem was one hundred years old when he became the father of Arpachshad\ntwo years after the flood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 11:11"}, "Shem lived five hundred years after he became the father of Arpachshad, and became the father of more sons and daughters.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 11:12"}, "Arpachshad lived thirty-five years and became the father of Shelah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 11:13"}, "Arpachshad lived four hundred and three years after he became the father of Shelah, and became the father of more sons\nand daughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 11:14"}, "Shelah lived thirty years, and became the father of Eber. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 11:15"}, "Shelah lived four hundred and three years after he became the father of Eber, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 11:16"}, "Eber lived thirty-four years, and became the father of Peleg.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 11:17"}, "Eber lived four hundred and thirty years after he became the father of Peleg, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 11:18"}, "Peleg lived thirty years, and became the father of Reu. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 11:19"}, "Peleg lived two hundred and nine years after he became the father of Reu, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 11:20"}, "Reu lived thirty-two years, and became the father of Serug.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 11:21"}, "Reu lived two hundred and seven years after he became the father of Serug, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 11:22"}, "Serug lived thirty years, and became the father of Nahor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 11:23"}, "Serug lived two hundred years after he became the father of Nahor, and became the father of more sons and daughters.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 11:24"}, "Nahor lived twenty-nine years, and became the father of Terah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 11:25"}, "Nahor lived one hundred and nineteen years after he became the father of Terah, and became the father of more sons and\ndaughters. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 11:26"}, "Terah lived seventy years, and became the father of Ibram, Nahor, and Haran.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 11:27"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of Terah. Terah became the father of Ibram, Nahor, and Haran. Haran became the\nfather of Lut. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 11:28"}, "Haran died in the land of his birth, in Ur of the Chaldees, while his father Terah was still alive.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 11:29"}, "Ibram and Nahor married wives. The name of Ibram\u2019s wife was Sarai, and the name of Nahor\u2019s wife was Milcah, the daughter\nof Haran, who was also the father of Iscah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 11:30"}, "Sarai was barren. She had no child. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 11:31"}, "Terah took Ibram his son, Lut the son of Haran, his son\u2019s son, and Sarai his daughter-in-law, his son Ibram\u2019s wife. They\nwent from Ur of the Chaldees, to go into the land of Canaan. They came to Haran and lived there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 11:32"}, "The days of Terah were two hundred and five years. Terah died in Haran.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 12:1"}, "Now the LORD said to Ibram, \u201cLeave your country, and your relatives, and your father\u2019s house, and go to the land that I\nwill show you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 12:2"}, "I will make of you a great nation. I will bless you and make your name great. You will be a blessing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 12:3"}, "I will bless those who bless you, and I will curse him who treats you with contempt. All the families of the earth will be\nblessed through you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 12:4"}, "So Ibram went, as the LORD had told him. Lut went with him. Ibram was seventy-five years old when he departed from Haran.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 12:5"}, "Ibram took Sarai his wife, Lut his brother\u2019s son, all their possessions that they had gathered, and the people whom they\nhad acquired in Haran, and they went to go into the land of Canaan. They entered into the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 12:6"}, "Ibram passed through the land to the place of Shechem, to the oak of Moreh. At that time, Canaanites were in the land.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 12:7"}, "The LORD appeared to Ibram and said, \u201cI will give this land to your offspring.\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He built an altar there to the LORD, who had appeared to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 12:8"}, "He left from there to go to the mountain on the east of Bethel and pitched his tent, having Bethel on the west, and Ai on\nthe east. There he built an altar to the LORD and called on the LORD\u2019s name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 12:9"}, "Ibram travelled, still going on towards the South. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 12:10"}, "There was a famine in the land. Ibram went down into Egypt to live as a foreigner there, for the famine was severe in the\nland. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 12:11"}, "When he had come near to enter Egypt, he said to Sarai his wife, \u201cSee now, I know that you are a beautiful woman to look\nat. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 12:12"}, "It will happen, when the Egyptians see you, that they will say, \u2018This is his wife.\u2019 They will kill me, but they will save\nyou alive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 12:13"}, "Please say that you are my sister, that it may be well with me for your sake, and that my soul may live because of you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 12:14"}, "When Ibram had come into Egypt, Egyptians saw that the woman was very beautiful.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 12:15"}, "The princes of Pharaoh saw her, and praised her to Pharaoh; and the woman was taken into Pharaoh\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 12:16"}, "He dealt well with Ibram for her sake. He had sheep, cattle, male donkeys, male servants, female servants, female\ndonkeys, and camels. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 12:17"}, "The LORD afflicted Pharaoh and his house with great plagues because of Sarai, Ibram\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 12:18"}, "Pharaoh called Ibram and said, \u201cWhat is this that you have done to me? Why didn\u2019t you tell me that she was your wife?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 12:19"}, "Why did you say, \u2018She is my sister,\u2019 so that I took her to be my wife? Now therefore, see your wife, take her, and go\nyour way.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 12:20"}, "Pharaoh commanded men concerning him, and they escorted him away with his wife and all that he had.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 13:1"}, "Ibram went up out of Egypt\u2014he, his wife, all that he had, and Lut with him\u2014into the South.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 13:2"}, "Ibram was very rich in livestock, in silver, and in gold. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 13:3"}, "He went on his journeys from the South as far as Bethel, to the place where his tent had been at the beginning, between\nBethel and Ai, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 13:4"}, "to the place of the altar, which he had made there at the first. There Ibram called on the LORD\u2019s name.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 13:5"}, "Lut also, who went with Ibram, had flocks, herds, and tents.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 13:6"}, "The land was not able to bear them, that they might live together; for their possessions were so great that they couldn\u2019t\nlive together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 13:7"}, "There was strife between the herdsmen of Ibram\u2019s livestock and the herdsmen of Lut\u2019s livestock. The Canaanites and the\nPerizzites lived in the land at that time. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 13:8"}, "Ibram said to Lut, \u201cPlease, let there be no strife between you and me, and between your herdsmen and my herdsmen; for we\nare relatives. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 13:9"}, "Isn\u2019t the whole land before you? Please separate yourself from me. If you go to the left hand, then I will go to the\nright. Or if you go to the right hand, then I will go to the left.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 13:10"}, "Lut lifted up his eyes, and saw all the plain of the Jordan, that it was well-watered everywhere, before the LORD\ndestroyed Sodom and Gomorrah, like the garden of the LORD, like the land of Egypt, as you go to Zoar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 13:11"}, "So Lut chose the Plain of the Jordan for himself. Lut travelled east, and they separated themselves from one other.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 13:12"}, "Ibram lived in the land of Canaan, and Lut lived in the cities of the plain, and moved his tent as far as Sodom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 13:13"}, "Now the men of Sodom were exceedingly wicked and sinners against the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 13:14"}, "The LORD said to Ibram, after Lut was separated from him, \u201cNow, lift up your eyes, and look from the place where you are,\nnorthward and southward and eastward and westward, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 13:15"}, "for I will give all the land which you see to you and to your offspring forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 13:16"}, "I will make your offspring as the dust of the earth, so that if a man can count the dust of the earth, then your\noffspring may also be counted. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 13:17"}, "Arise, walk through the land in its length and in its width; for I will give it to you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 13:18"}, "Ibram moved his tent, and came and lived by the oaks of Mamre, which are in Hebron, and built an altar there to the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 14:1"}, "In the days of Amraphel, king of Shinar; Arioch, king of Ellasar; Chedorlaomer, king of Elam; and Tidal, king of Goiim,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 14:2"}, "they made war with Bera, king of Sodom; Birsha, king of Gomorrah; Shinab, king of Admah; Shemeber, king of Zeboiim; and\nthe king of Bela (also called Zoar). \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 14:3"}, "All these joined together in the valley of Siddim (also called the Salt Sea).\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 14:4"}, "They served Chedorlaomer for twelve years, and in the thirteenth year they rebelled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 14:5"}, "In the fourteenth year Chedorlaomer came, and the kings who were with him, and struck the Rephaim in Ashteroth Karnaim,\nthe Zuzim in Ham, the Emim in Shaveh Kiriathaim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 14:6"}, "and the Horites in their Mount Seir, to El Paran, which is by the wilderness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 14:7"}, "They returned, and came to En Mishpat (also called Kadesh), and struck all the country of the Amalekites, and also the\nAmorites, that lived in Hazazon Tamar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 14:8"}, "The king of Sodom, and the king of Gomorrah, the king of Admah, the king of Zeboiim, and the king of Bela (also called\nZoar) went out; and they set the battle in array against them in the valley of Siddim\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 14:9"}, "against Chedorlaomer king of Elam, Tidal king of Goiim, Amraphel king of Shinar, and Arioch king of Ellasar; four kings\nagainst the five. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 14:10"}, "Now the valley of Siddim was full of tar pits; and the kings of Sodom and Gomorrah fled, and some fell there. Those who\nremained fled to the hills. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 14:11"}, "They took all the goods of Sodom and Gomorrah, and all their food, and went their way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 14:12"}, "They took Lut, Ibram\u2019s brother\u2019s son, who lived in Sodom, and his goods, and departed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 14:13"}, "One who had escaped came and told Ibram, the Hebrew. At that time, he lived by the oaks of Mamre, the Amorite, brother of\nEshcol and brother of Aner. They were allies of Ibram. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 14:14"}, "When Ibram heard that his relative was taken captive, he led out his three hundred and eighteen trained men, born in his\nhouse, and pursued as far as Dan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 14:15"}, "He divided himself against them by night, he and his servants, and struck them, and pursued them to Hobah, which is on\nthe left hand of Damascus. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 14:16"}, "He brought back all the goods, and also brought back his relative Lut and his goods, and the women also, and the other\npeople. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 14:17"}, "The king of Sodom went out to meet him after his return from the slaughter of Chedorlaomer and the kings who were with\nhim, at the valley of Shaveh (that is, the King\u2019s Valley). \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 14:18"}, "Melchizedek king of Salem brought out bread and wine. He was priest of Allah Most High.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 14:19"}, "He blessed him, and said, \u201cBlessed be Ibram of Allah Most High, possessor of heaven and earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 14:20"}, "Blessed be Allah Most High, who has delivered your enemies into your hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Ibram gave him a tenth of all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 14:21"}, "The king of Sodom said to Ibram, \u201cGive me the people, and take the goods for yourself.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 14:22"}, "Ibram said to the king of Sodom, \u201cI have lifted up my hand to the LORD, Allah Most High, possessor of heaven and earth,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 14:23"}, "that I will not take a thread nor a sandal strap nor anything that is yours, lest you should say, \u2018I have made Ibram\nrich.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 14:24"}, "I will accept nothing from you except that which the young men have eaten, and the portion of the men who went with me:\nAner, Eshcol, and Mamre. Let them take their portion.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 15:1"}, "After these things the LORD\u2019s word came to Ibram in a vision, saying, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, Ibram. I am your shield, your\nexceedingly great reward.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 15:2"}, "Ibram said, \u201cLord", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is\n\u201cAdonai\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ALLAH, what will you give me, since I go childless, and he who will inherit my estate is Eliezer of Damascus?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 15:3"}, "Ibram said, \u201cBehold, you have given no children to me: and, behold, one born in my house is my heir.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 15:4"}, "Behold, the LORD\u2019s word came to him, saying, \u201cThis man will not be your heir, but he who will come out of your own body\nwill be your heir.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 15:5"}, "The LORD brought him outside, and said, \u201cLook now towards the sky, and count the stars, if you are able to count them.\u201d He\nsaid to Ibram, \u201cSo your offspring will be.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 15:6"}, "He believed in the LORD, who credited it to him for righteousness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 15:7"}, "He said to Ibram, \u201cI am the LORD who brought you out of Ur of the Chaldees, to give you this land to inherit it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 15:8"}, "He said, \u201cLord ALLAH, how will I know that I will inherit it?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 15:9"}, "He said to him, \u201cBring me a heifer three years old, a female goat three years old, a ram three years old, a turtledove,\nand a young pigeon.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 15:10"}, "He brought him all these, and divided them in the middle, and laid each half opposite the other; but he didn\u2019t divide the\nbirds. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 15:11"}, "The birds of prey came down on the carcasses, and Ibram drove them away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 15:12"}, "When the sun was going down, a deep sleep fell on Ibram. Now terror and great darkness fell on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 15:13"}, "He said to Ibram, \u201cKnow for sure that your offspring will live as foreigners in a land that is not theirs, and will serve\nthem. They will afflict them four hundred years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 15:14"}, "I will also judge that nation, whom they will serve. Afterward they will come out with great wealth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 15:15"}, "but you will go to your fathers in peace. You will be buried at a good old age.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 15:16"}, "In the fourth generation they will come here again, for the iniquity of the Amorite is not yet full.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 15:17"}, "It came to pass that, when the sun went down, and it was dark, behold, a smoking furnace and a flaming torch passed\nbetween these pieces. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 15:18"}, "In that day the LORD made a covenant with Ibram, saying, \u201cI have given this land to your offspring, from the river of\nEgypt to the great river, the river Euphrates: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 15:19"}, "the land of the Kenites, the Kenizzites, the Kadmonites, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 15:20"}, "the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Rephaim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 15:21"}, "the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Girgashites, and the Jebusites.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 16:1"}, "Now Sarai, Ibram\u2019s wife, bore him no children. She had a servant, an Egyptian, whose name was Hajar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 16:2"}, "Sarai said to Ibram, \u201cSee now, the LORD has restrained me from bearing. Please go in to my servant. It may be that I will\nobtain children by her.\u201d Ibram listened to the voice of Sarai. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 16:3"}, "Sarai, Ibram\u2019s wife, took Hajar the Egyptian, her servant, after Ibram had lived ten years in the land of Canaan, and gave\nher to Ibram her husband to be his wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 16:4"}, "He went in to Hajar, and she conceived. When she saw that she had conceived, her mistress was despised in her eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 16:5"}, "Sarai said to Ibram, \u201cThis wrong is your fault. I gave my servant into your bosom, and when she saw that she had\nconceived, she despised me. May The LORD judge between me and you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 16:6"}, "But Ibram said to Sarai, \u201cBehold, your maid is in your hand. Do to her whatever is good in your eyes.\u201d Sarai dealt harshly\nwith her, and she fled from her face. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 16:7"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel found her by a fountain of water in the wilderness, by the fountain on the way to Shur.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 16:8"}, "He said, \u201cHajar, Sarai\u2019s servant, where did you come from? Where are you going?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cI am fleeing from the face of my mistress Sarai.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 16:9"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to her, \u201cReturn to your mistress, and submit yourself under her hands.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 16:10"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to her, \u201cI will greatly multiply your offspring, that they will not be counted for multitude.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 16:11"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel said to her, \u201cBehold, you are with child, and will bear a son. You shall call his name Ismail, because\nthe LORD has heard your affliction. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 16:12"}, "He will be like a wild donkey amongst men. His hand will be against every man, and every man\u2019s hand against him. He will\nlive opposed to all of his brothers.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 16:13"}, "She called the name of the LORD who spoke to her, \u201cYou are Allah who sees,\u201d for she said, \u201cHave I even stayed alive after\nseeing him?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 16:14"}, "Therefore the well was called Beer Lahai Roi.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:14\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Beer Lahai Roi means \u201cwell of the one who lives and sees me\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Behold, it is between Kadesh and Bered.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 16:15"}, "Hajar bore a son for Ibram. Ibram called the name of his son, whom Hajar bore, Ismail.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 16:16"}, "Ibram was eighty-six years old when Hajar bore Ismail to Ibram.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 17:1"}, "When Ibram was ninety-nine years old, the LORD appeared to Ibram and said to him, \u201cI am Allah Ta\u2019ala. Walk before me and\nbe blameless. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 17:2"}, "I will make my covenant between me and you, and will multiply you exceedingly.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 17:3"}, "Ibram fell on his face. Allah talked with him, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 17:4"}, "\u201cAs for me, behold, my covenant is with you. You will be the father of a multitude of nations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 17:5"}, "Your name will no more be called Ibram, but your name will be Ibrahim; for I have made you the father of a multitude of\nnations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 17:6"}, "I will make you exceedingly fruitful, and I will make nations of you. Kings will come out of you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 17:7"}, "I will establish my covenant between me and you and your offspring after you throughout their generations for an\neverlasting covenant, to be Allah to you and to your offspring after you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 17:8"}, "I will give to you, and to your offspring after you, the land where you are travelling, all the land of Canaan, for an\neverlasting possession. I will be their Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 17:9"}, "Allah said to Ibrahim, \u201cAs for you, you will keep my covenant, you and your offspring after you throughout their\ngenerations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 17:10"}, "This is my covenant, which you shall keep, between me and you and your offspring after you. Every male amongst you shall\nbe circumcised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 17:11"}, "You shall be circumcised in the flesh of your foreskin. It will be a token of the covenant between me and you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 17:12"}, "He who is eight days old will be circumcised amongst you, every male throughout your generations, he who is born in the\nhouse, or bought with money from any foreigner who is not of your offspring.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 17:13"}, "He who is born in your house, and he who is bought with your money, must be circumcised. My covenant will be in your\nflesh for an everlasting covenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 17:14"}, "The uncircumcised male who is not circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin, that soul shall be cut off from his people.\nHe has broken my covenant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 17:15"}, "Allah said to Ibrahim, \u201cAs for Sarai your wife, you shall not call her name Sarai, but her name will be Sarah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 17:16"}, "I will bless her, and moreover I will give you a son by her. Yes, I will bless her, and she will be a mother of nations.\nKings of peoples will come from her.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 17:17"}, "Then Ibrahim fell on his face, and laughed, and said in his heart, \u201cWill a child be born to him who is one hundred years\nold? Will Sarah, who is ninety years old, give birth?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 17:18"}, "Ibrahim said to Allah, \u201cOh that Ismail might live before you!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 17:19"}, "Allah said, \u201cNo, but Sarah, your wife, will bear you a son. You shall call his name\nIs\u1e25\u0101q.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["17:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Is\u1e25\u0101q means \u201che laughs\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I will establish my covenant with him for an everlasting covenant for his\noffspring after him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 17:20"}, "As for Ismail, I have heard you. Behold, I have blessed him, and will make him fruitful, and will multiply him\nexceedingly. He will become the father of twelve princes, and I will make him a great nation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 17:21"}, "But I will establish my covenant with Is\u1e25\u0101q, whom Sarah will bear to you at this set time next year.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 17:22"}, "When he finished talking with him, Allah went up from Ibrahim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 17:23"}, "Ibrahim took Ismail his son, all who were born in his house, and all who were bought with his money: every male amongst\nthe men of Ibrahim\u2019s house, and circumcised the flesh of their foreskin in the same day, as Allah had said to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 17:24"}, "Ibrahim was ninety-nine years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 17:25"}, "Ismail, his son, was thirteen years old when he was circumcised in the flesh of his foreskin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 17:26"}, "In the same day both Ibrahim and Ismail, his son, were circumcised.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 17:27"}, "All the men of his house, those born in the house, and those bought with money from a foreigner, were circumcised with\nhim. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 18:1"}, "The LORD appeared to him by the oaks of Mamre, as he sat in the tent door in the heat of the day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 18:2"}, "He lifted up his eyes and looked, and saw that three men stood near him. When he saw them, he ran to meet them from the\ntent door, and bowed himself to the earth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 18:3"}, "and said, \u201cMy lord, if now I have found favour in your sight, please don\u2019t go away from your servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 18:4"}, "Now let a little water be fetched, wash your feet, and rest yourselves under the tree.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 18:5"}, "I will get a piece of bread so you can refresh your heart. After that you may go your way, now that you have come to your\nservant.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cVery well, do as you have said.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 18:6"}, "Ibrahim hurried into the tent to Sarah, and said, \u201cQuickly prepare three\nseahs", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["18:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 seah is about 7 litres or 1.9 gallons or 0.8\npecks"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of fine meal, knead it, and make cakes.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 18:7"}, "Ibrahim ran to the herd, and fetched a tender and good calf, and gave it to the servant. He hurried to dress it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 18:8"}, "He took butter, milk, and the calf which he had dressed, and set it before them. He stood by them under the tree, and they\nate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 18:9"}, "They asked him, \u201cWhere is Sarah, your wife?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cThere, in the tent.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 18:10"}, "He said, \u201cI will certainly return to you at about this time next year; and behold, Sarah your wife will have a son.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Sarah heard in the tent door, which was behind him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 18:11"}, "Now Ibrahim and Sarah were old, well advanced in age. Sarah had passed the age of childbearing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 18:12"}, "Sarah laughed within herself, saying, \u201cAfter I have grown old will I have pleasure, my lord being old also?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 18:13"}, "The LORD said to Ibrahim, \u201cWhy did Sarah laugh, saying, \u2018Will I really bear a child when I am old?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 18:14"}, "Is anything too hard for the LORD? At the set time I will return to you, when the season comes round, and Sarah will have\na son.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 18:15"}, "Then Sarah denied it, saying, \u201cI didn\u2019t laugh,\u201d for she was afraid.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cNo, but you did laugh.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 18:16"}, "The men rose up from there, and looked towards Sodom. Ibrahim went with them to see them on their way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 18:17"}, "The LORD said, \u201cWill I hide from Ibrahim what I do, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 18:18"}, "since Ibrahim will surely become a great and mighty nation, and all the nations of the earth will be blessed in him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 18:19"}, "For I have known him, to the end that he may command his children and his household after him, that they may keep the way\nof the LORD, to do righteousness and justice; to the end that the LORD may bring on Ibrahim that which he has spoken of him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 18:20"}, "The LORD said, \u201cBecause the cry of Sodom and Gomorrah is great, and because their sin is very grievous,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 18:21"}, "I will go down now, and see whether their deeds are as bad as the reports which have come to me. If not, I will know.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 18:22"}, "The men turned from there, and went towards Sodom, but Ibrahim stood yet before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 18:23"}, "Ibrahim came near, and said, \u201cWill you consume the righteous with the wicked?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 18:24"}, "What if there are fifty righteous within the city? Will you consume and not spare the place for the fifty righteous who\nare in it? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 18:25"}, "May it be far from you to do things like that, to kill the righteous with the wicked, so that the righteous should be\nlike the wicked. May that be far from you. Shouldn\u2019t the Judge of all the earth do right?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 18:26"}, "The LORD said, \u201cIf I find in Sodom fifty righteous within the city, then I will spare the whole place for their sake.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 18:27"}, "Ibrahim answered, \u201cSee now, I have taken it on myself to speak to the Lord, although I am dust and ashes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 18:28"}, "What if there will lack five of the fifty righteous? Will you destroy all the city for lack of five?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will not destroy it if I find forty-five there.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 18:29"}, "He spoke to him yet again, and said, \u201cWhat if there are forty found there?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will not do it for the forty\u2019s sake.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 18:30"}, "He said, \u201cOh don\u2019t let the Lord be angry, and I will speak. What if there are thirty found there?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will not do it if I find thirty there.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 18:31"}, "He said, \u201cSee now, I have taken it on myself to speak to the Lord. What if there are twenty found there?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will not destroy it for the twenty\u2019s sake.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 18:32"}, "He said, \u201cOh don\u2019t let the Lord be angry, and I will speak just once more. What if ten are found there?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI will not destroy it for the ten\u2019s sake.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 18:33"}, "The LORD went his way, as soon as he had finished communing with Ibrahim, and Ibrahim returned to his place.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 19:1"}, "The two angels came to Sodom at evening. Lut sat in the gate of Sodom. Lut saw them, and rose up to meet them. He bowed\nhimself with his face to the earth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 19:2"}, "and he said, \u201cSee now, my lords, please come into your servant\u2019s house, stay all night, wash your feet, and you can rise\nup early, and go on your way.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cNo, but we will stay in the street all night.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 19:3"}, "He urged them greatly, and they came in with him, and entered into his house. He made them a feast, and baked unleavened\nbread, and they ate. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 19:4"}, "But before they lay down, the men of the city, the men of Sodom, surrounded the house, both young and old, all the people\nfrom every quarter. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 19:5"}, "They called to Lut, and said to him, \u201cWhere are the men who came in to you this night? Bring them out to us, that we may\nhave sex with them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 19:6"}, "Lut went out to them through the door, and shut the door after himself.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 19:7"}, "He said, \u201cPlease, my brothers, don\u2019t act so wickedly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 19:8"}, "See now, I have two virgin daughters. Please let me bring them out to you, and you may do to them what seems good to you.\nOnly don\u2019t do anything to these men, because they have come under the shadow of my roof.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 19:9"}, "They said, \u201cStand back!\u201d Then they said, \u201cThis one fellow came in to live as a foreigner, and he appoints himself a judge.\nNow we will deal worse with you than with them!\u201d They pressed hard on the man Lut, and came near to break the door.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 19:10"}, "But the men reached out their hand, and brought Lut into the house to them, and shut the door.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 19:11"}, "They struck the men who were at the door of the house with blindness, both small and great, so that they wearied\nthemselves to find the door. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 19:12"}, "The men said to Lut, \u201cDo you have anybody else here? Sons-in-law, your sons, your daughters, and whomever you have in the\ncity, bring them out of the place: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 19:13"}, "for we will destroy this place, because the outcry against them has grown so great before the LORD that the LORD has sent\nus to destroy it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 19:14"}, "Lut went out, and spoke to his sons-in-law, who were pledged to marry his daughters, and said, \u201cGet up! Get out of this\nplace, for the LORD will destroy the city!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But he seemed to his sons-in-law to be joking. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 19:15"}, "When the morning came, then the angels hurried Lut, saying, \u201cGet up! Take your wife and your two daughters who are here,\nlest you be consumed in the iniquity of the city.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 19:16"}, "But he lingered; and the men grabbed his hand, his wife\u2019s hand, and his two daughters\u2019 hands, the LORD being merciful to\nhim; and they took him out, and set him outside of the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 19:17"}, "It came to pass, when they had taken them out, that he said, \u201cEscape for your life! Don\u2019t look behind you, and don\u2019t stay\nanywhere in the plain. Escape to the mountains, lest you be consumed!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 19:18"}, "Lut said to them, \u201cOh, not so, my lord. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 19:19"}, "See now, your servant has found favour in your sight, and you have magnified your loving kindness, which you have shown\nto me in saving my life. I can\u2019t escape to the mountain, lest evil overtake me, and I die.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 19:20"}, "See now, this city is near to flee to, and it is a little one. Oh let me escape there (isn\u2019t it a little one?), and my\nsoul will live.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 19:21"}, "He said to him, \u201cBehold, I have granted your request concerning this thing also, that I will not overthrow the city of\nwhich you have spoken. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 19:22"}, "Hurry, escape there, for I can\u2019t do anything until you get there.\u201d Therefore the name of the city was called\nZoar.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["19:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Zoar means \u201clittle\u201d. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 19:23"}, "The sun had risen on the earth when Lut came to Zoar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 19:24"}, "Then the LORD rained on Sodom and on Gomorrah sulphur and fire from the LORD out of the sky.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 19:25"}, "He overthrew those cities, all the plain, all the inhabitants of the cities, and that which grew on the ground.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 19:26"}, "But Lut\u2019s wife looked back from behind him, and she became a pillar of salt.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 19:27"}, "Ibrahim went up early in the morning to the place where he had stood before the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 19:28"}, "He looked towards Sodom and Gomorrah, and towards all the land of the plain, and saw that the smoke of the land went up\nas the smoke of a furnace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 19:29"}, "When Allah destroyed the cities of the plain, Allah remembered Ibrahim, and sent Lut out of the middle of the overthrow,\nwhen he overthrew the cities in which Lut lived. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 19:30"}, "Lut went up out of Zoar, and lived in the mountain, and his two daughters with him; for he was afraid to live in Zoar. He\nlived in a cave with his two daughters. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 19:31"}, "The firstborn said to the younger, \u201cOur father is old, and there is not a man in the earth to come in to us in the way of\nall the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 19:32"}, "Come, let\u2019s make our father drink wine, and we will lie with him, that we may preserve our father\u2019s family line.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 19:33"}, "They made their father drink wine that night: and the firstborn went in, and lay with her father. He didn\u2019t know when she\nlay down, nor when she arose. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 19:34"}, "It came to pass on the next day, that the firstborn said to the younger, \u201cBehold, I lay last night with my father. Let\u2019s\nmake him drink wine again tonight. You go in, and lie with him, that we may preserve our father\u2019s family line.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 19:35"}, "They made their father drink wine that night also. The younger went and lay with him. He didn\u2019t know when she lay down,\nnor when she got up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 19:36"}, "Thus both of Lut\u2019s daughters were with child by their father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 19:37"}, "The firstborn bore a son, and named him Moab. He is the father of the Moabites to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 19:38"}, "The younger also bore a son, and called his name Ben Ammi. He is the father of the children of Ammon to this day.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 20:1"}, "Ibrahim travelled from there towards the land of the South, and lived between Kadesh and Shur. He lived as a foreigner in\nGerar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 20:2"}, "Ibrahim said about Sarah his wife, \u201cShe is my sister.\u201d Abimelech king of Gerar sent, and took Sarah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 20:3"}, "But Allah came to Abimelech in a dream of the night, and said to him, \u201cBehold, you are a dead man, because of the woman\nwhom you have taken; for she is a man\u2019s wife.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 20:4"}, "Now Abimelech had not come near her. He said, \u201cLord, will you kill even a righteous nation?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 20:5"}, "Didn\u2019t he tell me, \u2018She is my sister\u2019? She, even she herself, said, \u2018He is my brother.\u2019 I have done this in the integrity\nof my heart and the innocence of my hands.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 20:6"}, "Allah said to him in the dream, \u201cYes, I know that in the integrity of your heart you have done this, and I also withheld\nyou from sinning against me. Therefore I didn\u2019t allow you to touch her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 20:7"}, "Now therefore, restore the man\u2019s wife. For he is a prophet, and he will pray for you, and you will live. If you don\u2019t\nrestore her, know for sure that you will die, you, and all who are yours.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 20:8"}, "Abimelech rose early in the morning, and called all his servants, and told all these things in their ear. The men were\nvery scared. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 20:9"}, "Then Abimelech called Ibrahim, and said to him, \u201cWhat have you done to us? How have I sinned against you, that you have\nbrought on me and on my kingdom a great sin? You have done deeds to me that ought not to be done!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 20:10"}, "Abimelech said to Ibrahim, \u201cWhat did you see, that you have done this thing?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 20:11"}, "Ibrahim said, \u201cBecause I thought, \u2018Surely the fear of Allah is not in this place. They will kill me for my wife\u2019s sake.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 20:12"}, "Besides, she is indeed my sister, the daughter of my father, but not the daughter of my mother; and she became my wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 20:13"}, "When Allah caused me to wander from my father\u2019s house, I said to her, \u2018This is your kindness which you shall show to me.\nEverywhere that we go, say of me, \u201cHe is my brother.\u201d\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 20:14"}, "Abimelech took sheep and cattle, male servants and female servants, and gave them to Ibrahim, and restored Sarah, his\nwife, to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 20:15"}, "Abimelech said, \u201cBehold, my land is before you. Dwell where it pleases you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 20:16"}, "To Sarah he said, \u201cBehold, I have given your brother a thousand pieces of silver. Behold, it is for you a covering of the\neyes to all that are with you. In front of all you are vindicated.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 20:17"}, "Ibrahim prayed to Allah. Allah healed Abimelech, and his wife, and his female servants, and they bore children.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 20:18"}, "For the LORD had closed up tight all the wombs of the house of Abimelech, because of Sarah, Ibrahim\u2019s wife.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 21:1"}, "The LORD visited Sarah as he had said, and the LORD did to Sarah as he had spoken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 21:2"}, "Sarah conceived, and bore Ibrahim a son in his old age, at the set time of which Allah had spoken to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 21:3"}, "Ibrahim called his son who was born to him, whom Sarah bore to him, Is\u1e25\u0101q.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Is\u1e25\u0101q means \u201cHe laughs\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 21:4"}, "Ibrahim circumcised his son, Is\u1e25\u0101q, when he was eight days old, as Allah had commanded him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 21:5"}, "Ibrahim was one hundred years old when his son, Is\u1e25\u0101q, was born to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 21:6"}, "Sarah said, \u201cAllah has made me laugh. Everyone who hears will laugh with me.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 21:7"}, "She said, \u201cWho would have said to Ibrahim that Sarah would nurse children? For I have borne him a son in his old age.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 21:8"}, "The child grew and was weaned. Ibrahim made a great feast on the day that Is\u1e25\u0101q was weaned.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 21:9"}, "Sarah saw the son of Hajar the Egyptian, whom she had borne to Ibrahim, mocking.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 21:10"}, "Therefore she said to Ibrahim, \u201cCast out this servant and her son! For the son of this servant will not be heir with my\nson, Is\u1e25\u0101q.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 21:11"}, "The thing was very grievous in Ibrahim\u2019s sight on account of his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 21:12"}, "Allah said to Ibrahim, \u201cDon\u2019t let it be grievous in your sight because of the boy, and because of your servant. In all\nthat Sarah says to you, listen to her voice. For your offspring will be named through Is\u1e25\u0101q.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 21:13"}, "I will also make a nation of the son of the servant, because he is your child.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 21:14"}, "Ibrahim rose up early in the morning, and took bread and a container of water, and gave it to Hajar, putting it on her\nshoulder; and gave her the child, and sent her away. She departed, and wandered in the wilderness of Beersheba.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 21:15"}, "The water in the container was spent, and she put the child under one of the shrubs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 21:16"}, "She went and sat down opposite him, a good way off, about a bow shot away. For she said, \u201cDon\u2019t let me see the death of\nthe child.\u201d She sat opposite him, and lifted up her voice, and wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 21:17"}, "Allah heard the voice of the boy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The angel of Allah called to Hajar out of the sky, and said to her, \u201cWhat troubles you, Hajar? Don\u2019t be afraid. For Allah\nhas heard the voice of the boy where he is. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 21:18"}, "Get up, lift up the boy, and hold him with your hand. For I will make him a great nation.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 21:19"}, "Allah opened her eyes, and she saw a well of water. She went, filled the container with water, and gave the boy a drink.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 21:20"}, "Allah was with the boy, and he grew. He lived in the wilderness, and as he grew up, became an archer.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 21:21"}, "He lived in the wilderness of Paran. His mother got a wife for him out of the land of Egypt.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 21:22"}, "At that time, Abimelech and Phicol the captain of his army spoke to Ibrahim, saying, \u201cAllah is with you in all that you\ndo. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 21:23"}, "Now, therefore, swear to me here by Allah that you will not deal falsely with me, nor with my son, nor with my son\u2019s son.\nBut according to the kindness that I have done to you, you shall do to me, and to the land in which you have lived as a\nforeigner.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 21:24"}, "Ibrahim said, \u201cI will swear.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 21:25"}, "Ibrahim complained to Abimelech because of a water well, which Abimelech\u2019s servants had violently taken away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 21:26"}, "Abimelech said, \u201cI don\u2019t know who has done this thing. You didn\u2019t tell me, and I didn\u2019t hear of it until today.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 21:27"}, "Ibrahim took sheep and cattle, and gave them to Abimelech. Those two made a covenant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 21:28"}, "Ibrahim set seven ewe lambs of the flock by themselves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 21:29"}, "Abimelech said to Ibrahim, \u201cWhat do these seven ewe lambs, which you have set by themselves, mean?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 21:30"}, "He said, \u201cYou shall take these seven ewe lambs from my hand, that it may be a witness to me, that I have dug this well.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 21:31"}, "Therefore he called that place Beersheba,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["21:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Beersheba can mean \u201cwell of the oath\u201d or \u201cwell of\nseven\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " because they both swore an oath there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 21:32"}, "So they made a covenant at Beersheba. Abimelech rose up with Phicol, the captain of his army, and they returned into the\nland of the Philistines. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 21:33"}, "Ibrahim planted a tamarisk tree in Beersheba, and called there on the name of the LORD, the Everlasting Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 21:34"}, "Ibrahim lived as a foreigner in the land of the Philistines many days.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 22:1"}, "After these things, Allah tested Ibrahim, and said to him, \u201cIbrahim!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 22:2"}, "He said, \u201cNow take your son, your only son, Is\u1e25\u0101q, whom you love, and go into the land of Moriah. Offer him there as a\nburnt offering on one of the mountains which I will tell you of.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 22:3"}, "Ibrahim rose early in the morning, and saddled his donkey; and took two of his young men with him, and Is\u1e25\u0101q his son. He\nsplit the wood for the burnt offering, and rose up, and went to the place of which Allah had told him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 22:4"}, "On the third day Ibrahim lifted up his eyes, and saw the place far off.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 22:5"}, "Ibrahim said to his young men, \u201cStay here with the donkey. The boy and I will go over there. We will worship, and come\nback to you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 22:6"}, "Ibrahim took the wood of the burnt offering and laid it on Is\u1e25\u0101q his son. He took in his hand the fire and the knife. They\nboth went together. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 22:7"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q spoke to Ibrahim his father, and said, \u201cMy father?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am, my son.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere is the fire and the wood, but where is the lamb for a burnt offering?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 22:8"}, "Ibrahim said, \u201cAllah will provide himself the lamb for a burnt offering, my son.\u201d So they both went together.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 22:9"}, "They came to the place which Allah had told him of. Ibrahim built the altar there, and laid the wood in order, bound Is\u1e25\u0101q\nhis son, and laid him on the altar, on the wood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 22:10"}, "Ibrahim stretched out his hand, and took the knife to kill his son.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 22:11"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel called to him out of the sky, and said, \u201cIbrahim, Ibrahim!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 22:12"}, "He said, \u201cDon\u2019t lay your hand on the boy or do anything to him. For now I know that you fear Allah, since you have not\nwithheld your son, your only son, from me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 22:13"}, "Ibrahim lifted up his eyes, and looked, and saw that behind him was a ram caught in the thicket by his horns. Ibrahim\nwent and took the ram, and offered him up for a burnt offering instead of his son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 22:14"}, "Ibrahim called the name of that place \u201cthe LORD Will Provide\u201d.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["22:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, the LORD Jireh, or, the LORD Seeing"]}], "caller": "+"}, " As it is said to this day, \u201cOn The LORD\u2019s mountain, it will be\nprovided.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 22:15"}, "The LORD\u2019s angel called to Ibrahim a second time out of the sky,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 22:16"}, "and said, \u201c\u2018I have sworn by myself,\u2019 says the LORD, \u2018because you have done this thing, and have not withheld your son,\nyour only son, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 22:17"}, "that I will bless you greatly, and I will multiply your offspring greatly like the stars of the heavens, and like the\nsand which is on the seashore. Your offspring will possess the gate of his enemies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 22:18"}, "All the nations of the earth will be blessed by your offspring, because you have obeyed my voice.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 22:19"}, "So Ibrahim returned to his young men, and they rose up and went together to Beersheba. Ibrahim lived at Beersheba.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 22:20"}, "After these things, Ibrahim was told, \u201cBehold, Milcah, she also has borne children to your brother Nahor:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 22:21"}, "Uz his firstborn, Buz his brother, Kemuel the father of Aram,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 22:22"}, "Chesed, Hazo, Pildash, Jidlaph, and Bethuel.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 22:23"}, "Bethuel became the father of Rebekah. These eight Milcah bore to Nahor, Ibrahim\u2019s brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 22:24"}, "His concubine, whose name was Reumah, also bore Tebah, Gaham, Tahash, and Maacah.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 23:1"}, "Sarah lived one hundred and twenty-seven years. This was the length of Sarah\u2019s life.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 23:2"}, "Sarah died in Kiriath Arba (also called Hebron), in the land of Canaan. Ibrahim came to mourn for Sarah, and to weep for\nher. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 23:3"}, "Ibrahim rose up from before his dead and spoke to the children of Heth, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 23:4"}, "\u201cI am a stranger and a foreigner living with you. Give me a possession of a burying-place with you, that I may bury my\ndead out of my sight.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 23:5"}, "The children of Heth answered Ibrahim, saying to him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 23:6"}, "\u201cHear us, my lord. You are a prince of Allah amongst us. Bury your dead in the best of our tombs. None of us will withhold\nfrom you his tomb. Bury your dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 23:7"}, "Ibrahim rose up, and bowed himself to the people of the land, to the children of Heth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 23:8"}, "He talked with them, saying, \u201cIf you agree that I should bury my dead out of my sight, hear me, and entreat for me to\nEphron the son of Zohar, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 23:9"}, "that he may sell me the cave of Machpelah, which he has, which is in the end of his field. For the full price let him sell\nit to me amongst you as a possession for a burial place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 23:10"}, "Now Ephron was sitting in the middle of the children of Heth. Ephron the Hittite answered Ibrahim in the hearing of the\nchildren of Heth, even of all who went in at the gate of his city, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 23:11"}, "\u201cNo, my lord, hear me. I give you the field, and I give you the cave that is in it. In the presence of the children of my\npeople I give it to you. Bury your dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 23:12"}, "Ibrahim bowed himself down before the people of the land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 23:13"}, "He spoke to Ephron in the audience of the people of the land, saying, \u201cBut if you will, please hear me. I will give the\nprice of the field. Take it from me, and I will bury my dead there.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 23:14"}, "Ephron answered Ibrahim, saying to him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 23:15"}, "\u201cMy lord, listen to me. What is a piece of land worth four hundred shekels of\nsilver", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["23:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams, so 400 shekels would be about 4 kg. or 8.8\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " between me and you? Therefore bury your dead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 23:16"}, "Ibrahim listened to Ephron. Ibrahim weighed to Ephron the silver which he had named in the hearing of the children of\nHeth, four hundred shekels of silver, according to the current merchants\u2019 standard.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 23:17"}, "So the field of Ephron, which was in Machpelah, which was before Mamre, the field, the cave which was in it, and all the\ntrees that were in the field, that were in all of its borders, were deeded\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 23:18"}, "to Ibrahim for a possession in the presence of the children of Heth, before all who went in at the gate of his city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 23:19"}, "After this, Ibrahim buried Sarah his wife in the cave of the field of Machpelah before Mamre (that is, Hebron), in the\nland of Canaan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 23:20"}, "The field, and the cave that is in it, were deeded to Ibrahim by the children of Heth as a possession for a burial place.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 24:1"}, "Ibrahim was old, and well advanced in age. The LORD had blessed Ibrahim in all things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 24:2"}, "Ibrahim said to his servant, the elder of his house, who ruled over all that he had, \u201cPlease put your hand under my thigh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 24:3"}, "I will make you swear by the LORD, Allah of heaven and Allah of the earth, that you shall not take a wife for my son of\nthe daughters of the Canaanites, amongst whom I live. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 24:4"}, "But you shall go to my country, and to my relatives, and take a wife for my son Is\u1e25\u0101q.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 24:5"}, "The servant said to him, \u201cWhat if the woman isn\u2019t willing to follow me to this land? Must I bring your son again to the\nland you came from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 24:6"}, "Ibrahim said to him, \u201cBeware that you don\u2019t bring my son there again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 24:7"}, "The LORD, Allah of heaven\u2014who took me from my father\u2019s house, and from the land of my birth, who spoke to me, and who\nswore to me, saying, \u2018I will give this land to your offspring\u2014he will send his angel before you, and you shall take a wife for\nmy son from there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 24:8"}, "If the woman isn\u2019t willing to follow you, then you shall be clear from this oath to me. Only you shall not bring my son\nthere again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 24:9"}, "The servant put his hand under the thigh of Ibrahim his master, and swore to him concerning this matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 24:10"}, "The servant took ten of his master\u2019s camels, and departed, having a variety of good things of his master\u2019s with him. He\narose, and went to Mesopotamia, to the city of Nahor. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 24:11"}, "He made the camels kneel down outside the city by the well of water at the time of evening, the time that women go out to\ndraw water. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 24:12"}, "He said, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of my master Ibrahim, please give me success today, and show kindness to my master Ibrahim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 24:13"}, "Behold, I am standing by the spring of water. The daughters of the men of the city are coming out to draw water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 24:14"}, "Let it happen, that the young lady to whom I will say, \u2018Please let down your pitcher, that I may drink,\u2019 then she says,\n\u2018Drink, and I will also give your camels a drink,\u2019\u2014let her be the one you have appointed for your servant Is\u1e25\u0101q. By this I will\nknow that you have shown kindness to my master.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 24:15"}, "Before he had finished speaking, behold, Rebekah came out, who was born to Bethuel the son of Milcah, the wife of Nahor,\nIbrahim\u2019s brother, with her pitcher on her shoulder. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 24:16"}, "The young lady was very beautiful to look at, a virgin. No man had known her. She went down to the spring, filled her\npitcher, and came up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 24:17"}, "The servant ran to meet her, and said, \u201cPlease give me a drink, a little water from your pitcher.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 24:18"}, "She said, \u201cDrink, my lord.\u201d She hurried, and let down her pitcher on her hand, and gave him a drink.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 24:19"}, "When she had finished giving him a drink, she said, \u201cI will also draw for your camels, until they have finished\ndrinking.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 24:20"}, "She hurried, and emptied her pitcher into the trough, and ran again to the well to draw, and drew for all his camels.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 24:21"}, "The man looked steadfastly at her, remaining silent, to know whether the LORD had made his journey prosperous or not.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 24:22"}, "As the camels had done drinking, the man took a golden ring of half a\nshekel", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["24:22 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}], "caller": "+"}, " weight, and two bracelets for her hands of ten shekels weight of gold,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 24:23"}, "and said, \u201cWhose daughter are you? Please tell me. Is there room in your father\u2019s house for us to stay?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 24:24"}, "She said to him, \u201cI am the daughter of Bethuel the son of Milcah, whom she bore to Nahor.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 24:25"}, "She said moreover to him, \u201cWe have both straw and feed enough, and room to lodge in.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 24:26"}, "The man bowed his head, and worshipped the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 24:27"}, "He said, \u201cBlessed be the LORD, Allah of my master Ibrahim, who has not forsaken his loving kindness and his truth towards\nmy master. As for me, the LORD has led me on the way to the house of my master\u2019s relatives.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 24:28"}, "The young lady ran, and told her mother\u2019s house about these words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 24:29"}, "Rebekah had a brother, and his name was Laban. Laban ran out to the man, to the spring.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 24:30"}, "When he saw the ring, and the bracelets on his sister\u2019s hands, and when he heard the words of Rebekah his sister, saying,\n\u201cThis is what the man said to me,\u201d he came to the man. Behold, he was standing by the camels at the spring.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 24:31"}, "He said, \u201cCome in, you blessed of the LORD. Why do you stand outside? For I have prepared the house, and room for the\ncamels.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 24:32"}, "The man came into the house, and he unloaded the camels. He gave straw and feed for the camels, and water to wash his\nfeet and the feet of the men who were with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 24:33"}, "Food was set before him to eat, but he said, \u201cI will not eat until I have told my message.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Laban said, \u201cSpeak on.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 24:34"}, "He said, \u201cI am Ibrahim\u2019s servant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 24:35"}, "The LORD has blessed my master greatly. He has become great. The LORD has given him flocks and herds, silver and gold,\nmale servants and female servants, and camels and donkeys. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 24:36"}, "Sarah, my master\u2019s wife, bore a son to my master when she was old. He has given all that he has to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 24:37"}, "My master made me swear, saying, \u2018You shall not take a wife for my son from the daughters of the Canaanites, in whose\nland I live, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 24:38"}, "but you shall go to my father\u2019s house, and to my relatives, and take a wife for my son.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 24:39"}, "I asked my master, \u2018What if the woman will not follow me?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 24:40"}, "He said to me, \u2018The LORD, before whom I walk, will send his angel with you, and prosper your way. You shall take a wife\nfor my son from my relatives, and of my father\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 24:41"}, "Then you will be clear from my oath, when you come to my relatives. If they don\u2019t give her to you, you shall be clear\nfrom my oath.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 24:42"}, "I came today to the spring, and said, \u2018The LORD, Allah of my master Ibrahim, if now you do prosper my way which I go\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 24:43"}, "behold, I am standing by this spring of water. Let it happen, that the maiden who comes out to draw, to whom I will say,\n\u201cPlease give me a little water from your pitcher to drink,\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "GEN 24:44"}, "then she tells me, \u201cDrink, and I will also draw for your camels,\u201d\u2014let her be the woman whom the LORD has appointed for my\nmaster\u2019s son.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "GEN 24:45"}, "Before I had finished speaking in my heart, behold, Rebekah came out with her pitcher on her shoulder. She went down to\nthe spring, and drew. I said to her, \u2018Please let me drink.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "GEN 24:46"}, "She hurried and let down her pitcher from her shoulder, and said, \u2018Drink, and I will also give your camels a drink.\u2019 So I\ndrank, and she also gave the camels a drink. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "GEN 24:47"}, "I asked her, and said, \u2018Whose daughter are you?\u2019 She said, \u2018The daughter of Bethuel, Nahor\u2019s son, whom Milcah bore to\nhim.\u2019 I put the ring on her nose, and the bracelets on her hands.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "GEN 24:48"}, "I bowed my head, and worshipped the LORD, and blessed the LORD, Allah of my master Ibrahim, who had led me in the right\nway to take my master\u2019s brother\u2019s daughter for his son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "GEN 24:49"}, "Now if you will deal kindly and truly with my master, tell me. If not, tell me, that I may turn to the right hand, or to\nthe left.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "GEN 24:50"}, "Then Laban and Bethuel answered, \u201cThe thing proceeds from the LORD. We can\u2019t speak to you bad or good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "GEN 24:51"}, "Behold, Rebekah is before you. Take her, and go, and let her be your master\u2019s son\u2019s wife, as the LORD has spoken.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "GEN 24:52"}, "When Ibrahim\u2019s servant heard their words, he bowed himself down to the earth to the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "GEN 24:53"}, "The servant brought out jewels of silver, and jewels of gold, and clothing, and gave them to Rebekah. He also gave\nprecious things to her brother and her mother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "GEN 24:54"}, "They ate and drank, he and the men who were with him, and stayed all night. They rose up in the morning, and he said,\n\u201cSend me away to my master.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "GEN 24:55"}, "Her brother and her mother said, \u201cLet the young lady stay with us a few days, at least ten. After that she will go.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "GEN 24:56"}, "He said to them, \u201cDon\u2019t hinder me, since the LORD has prospered my way. Send me away that I may go to my master.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "GEN 24:57"}, "They said, \u201cWe will call the young lady, and ask her.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "GEN 24:58"}, "They called Rebekah, and said to her, \u201cWill you go with this man?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cI will go.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "GEN 24:59"}, "They sent away Rebekah, their sister, with her nurse, Ibrahim\u2019s servant, and his men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "GEN 24:60"}, "They blessed Rebekah, and said to her, \u201cOur sister, may you be the mother of thousands of ten thousands, and let your\noffspring possess the gate of those who hate them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "GEN 24:61"}, "Rebekah arose with her ladies. They rode on the camels, and followed the man. The servant took Rebekah, and went his way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "GEN 24:62"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q came from the way of Beer Lahai Roi, for he lived in the land of the South.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "GEN 24:63"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q went out to meditate in the field at the evening. He lifted up his eyes and looked. Behold, there were camels\ncoming. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "GEN 24:64"}, "Rebekah lifted up her eyes, and when she saw Is\u1e25\u0101q, she got off the camel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "GEN 24:65"}, "She said to the servant, \u201cWho is the man who is walking in the field to meet us?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The servant said, \u201cIt is my master.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She took her veil, and covered herself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "GEN 24:66"}, "The servant told Is\u1e25\u0101q all the things that he had done. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "GEN 24:67"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q brought her into his mother Sarah\u2019s tent, and took Rebekah, and she became his wife. He loved her. So Is\u1e25\u0101q was\ncomforted after his mother\u2019s death. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 25:1"}, "Ibrahim took another wife, and her name was Keturah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 25:2"}, "She bore him Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 25:3"}, "Jokshan became the father of Sheba, and Dedan. The sons of Dedan were Asshurim, Letushim, and Leummim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 25:4"}, "The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 25:5"}, "Ibrahim gave all that he had to Is\u1e25\u0101q, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 25:6"}, "but Ibrahim gave gifts to the sons of Ibrahim\u2019s concubines. While he still lived, he sent them away from Is\u1e25\u0101q his son,\neastward, to the east country. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 25:7"}, "These are the days of the years of Ibrahim\u2019s life which he lived: one hundred and seventy-five years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 25:8"}, "Ibrahim gave up his spirit, and died at a good old age, an old man, and full of years, and was gathered to his people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 25:9"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q and Ismail, his sons, buried him in the cave of Machpelah, in the field of Ephron, the son of Zohar the Hittite,\nwhich is near Mamre, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 25:10"}, "the field which Ibrahim purchased from the children of Heth. Ibrahim was buried there with Sarah, his wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 25:11"}, "After the death of Ibrahim, Allah blessed Is\u1e25\u0101q, his son. Is\u1e25\u0101q lived by Beer Lahai Roi.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 25:12"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of Ismail, Ibrahim\u2019s son, whom Hajar the Egyptian, Sarah\u2019s servant, bore to\nIbrahim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 25:13"}, "These are the names of the sons of Ismail, by their names, according to the order of their birth: the firstborn of\nIsmail, Nebaioth, then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 25:14"}, "Mishma, Dumah, Massa, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 25:15"}, "Hadad, Tema, Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 25:16"}, "These are the sons of Ismail, and these are their names, by their villages, and by their encampments: twelve princes,\naccording to their nations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 25:17"}, "These are the years of the life of Ismail: one hundred and thirty-seven years. He gave up his spirit and died, and was\ngathered to his people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 25:18"}, "They lived from Havilah to Shur that is before Egypt, as you go towards Assyria. He lived opposite all his relatives.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 25:19"}, "This is the history of the generations of Is\u1e25\u0101q, Ibrahim\u2019s son. Ibrahim became the father of Is\u1e25\u0101q.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 25:20"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q was forty years old when he took Rebekah, the daughter of Bethuel the Syrian of Paddan Aram, the sister of Laban\nthe Syrian, to be his wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 25:21"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q entreated the LORD for his wife, because she was barren. The LORD was entreated by him, and Rebekah his wife\nconceived. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 25:22"}, "The children struggled together within her. She said, \u201cIf it is like this, why do I live?\u201d She went to enquire of the\nLORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 25:23"}, "The LORD said to her, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cTwo nations are in your womb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Two peoples will be separated from your body. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The one people will be stronger than the other people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The elder will serve the younger.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 25:24"}, "When her days to be delivered were fulfilled, behold, there were twins in her womb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 25:25"}, "The first came out red all over, like a hairy garment. They named him Esau.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 25:26"}, "After that, his brother came out, and his hand had hold on Esau\u2019s heel. He was named Yaqub. Is\u1e25\u0101q was sixty years old\nwhen she bore them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 25:27"}, "The boys grew. Esau was a skilful hunter, a man of the field. Yaqub was a quiet man, living in tents.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 25:28"}, "Now Is\u1e25\u0101q loved Esau, because he ate his venison. Rebekah loved Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 25:29"}, "Yaqub boiled stew. Esau came in from the field, and he was famished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 25:30"}, "Esau said to Yaqub, \u201cPlease feed me with some of that red stew, for I am famished.\u201d Therefore his name was called\nEdom.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cEdom\u201d means \u201cred\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 25:31"}, "Yaqub said, \u201cFirst, sell me your birthright.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 25:32"}, "Esau said, \u201cBehold, I am about to die. What good is the birthright to me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 25:33"}, "Yaqub said, \u201cSwear to me first.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He swore to him. He sold his birthright to Yaqub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 25:34"}, "Yaqub gave Esau bread and lentil stew. He ate and drank, rose up, and went his way. So Esau despised his birthright.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 26:1"}, "There was a famine in the land, in addition to the first famine that was in the days of Ibrahim. Is\u1e25\u0101q went to Abimelech\nking of the Philistines, to Gerar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 26:2"}, "The LORD appeared to him, and said, \u201cDon\u2019t go down into Egypt. Live in the land I will tell you about.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 26:3"}, "Live in this land, and I will be with you, and will bless you. For I will give to you, and to your offspring, all these\nlands, and I will establish the oath which I swore to Ibrahim your father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 26:4"}, "I will multiply your offspring as the stars of the sky, and will give all these lands to your offspring. In your offspring\nall the nations of the earth will be blessed, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 26:5"}, "because Ibrahim obeyed my voice, and kept my requirements, my commandments, my statutes, and my laws.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 26:6"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q lived in Gerar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 26:7"}, "The men of the place asked him about his wife. He said, \u201cShe is my sister,\u201d for he was afraid to say, \u201cMy wife\u201d, lest, he\nthought, \u201cthe men of the place might kill me for Rebekah, because she is beautiful to look at.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 26:8"}, "When he had been there a long time, Abimelech king of the Philistines looked out at a window, and saw, and, behold, Is\u1e25\u0101q\nwas caressing Rebekah, his wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 26:9"}, "Abimelech called Is\u1e25\u0101q, and said, \u201cBehold, surely she is your wife. Why did you say, \u2018She is my sister?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Is\u1e25\u0101q said to him, \u201cBecause I said, \u2018Lest I die because of her.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 26:10"}, "Abimelech said, \u201cWhat is this you have done to us? One of the people might easily have lain with your wife, and you would\nhave brought guilt on us!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 26:11"}, "Abimelech commanded all the people, saying, \u201cHe who touches this man or his wife will surely be put to death.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 26:12"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q sowed in that land, and reaped in the same year one hundred times what he planted. The LORD blessed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 26:13"}, "The man grew great, and grew more and more until he became very great.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 26:14"}, "He had possessions of flocks, possessions of herds, and a great household. The Philistines envied him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 26:15"}, "Now all the wells which his father\u2019s servants had dug in the days of Ibrahim his father, the Philistines had stopped, and\nfilled with earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 26:16"}, "Abimelech said to Is\u1e25\u0101q, \u201cGo away from us, for you are much mightier than we.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 26:17"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q departed from there, encamped in the valley of Gerar, and lived there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 26:18"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q dug again the wells of water, which they had dug in the days of Ibrahim his father, for the Philistines had stopped\nthem after the death of Ibrahim. He called their names after the names by which his father had called them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 26:19"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q\u2019s servants dug in the valley, and found there a well of springing water.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 26:20"}, "The herdsmen of Gerar argued with Is\u1e25\u0101q\u2019s herdsmen, saying, \u201cThe water is ours.\u201d He called the name of the well Esek,\nbecause they contended with him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 26:21"}, "They dug another well, and they argued over that, also. He called its name Sitnah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 26:22"}, "He left that place, and dug another well. They didn\u2019t argue over that one. He called it Rehoboth. He said, \u201cFor now the\nLORD has made room for us, and we will be fruitful in the land.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 26:23"}, "He went up from there to Beersheba. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 26:24"}, "The LORD appeared to him the same night, and said, \u201cI am Allah of Ibrahim your father. Don\u2019t be afraid, for I am with\nyou, and will bless you, and multiply your offspring for my servant Ibrahim\u2019s sake.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 26:25"}, "He built an altar there, and called on the LORD\u2019s name, and pitched his tent there. There Is\u1e25\u0101q\u2019s servants dug a well.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 26:26"}, "Then Abimelech went to him from Gerar, and Ahuzzath his friend, and Phicol the captain of his army.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 26:27"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q said to them, \u201cWhy have you come to me, since you hate me, and have sent me away from you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 26:28"}, "They said, \u201cWe saw plainly that the LORD was with you. We said, \u2018Let there now be an oath between us, even between us and\nyou, and let\u2019s make a covenant with you, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 26:29"}, "that you will do us no harm, as we have not touched you, and as we have done to you nothing but good, and have sent you\naway in peace.\u2019 You are now the blessed of the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 26:30"}, "He made them a feast, and they ate and drank. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 26:31"}, "They rose up some time in the morning, and swore an oath to one another. Is\u1e25\u0101q sent them away, and they departed from him\nin peace. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 26:32"}, "The same day, Is\u1e25\u0101q\u2019s servants came, and told him concerning the well which they had dug, and said to him, \u201cWe have found\nwater.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 26:33"}, "He called it \u201cShibah\u201d.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["26:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Shibah means \u201coath\u201d or\n\u201cseven\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Therefore the name of the city is \u201cBeersheba\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["26:33\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Beersheba means \u201cwell of the oath\u201d or \u201cwell of the seven\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " to this day.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 26:34"}, "When Esau was forty years old, he took as wife Judith, the daughter of Beeri the Hittite, and Basemath, the daughter of\nElon the Hittite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 26:35"}, "They grieved Is\u1e25\u0101q\u2019s and Rebekah\u2019s spirits. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 27:1"}, "When Is\u1e25\u0101q was old, and his eyes were dim, so that he could not see, he called Esau his elder son, and said to him, \u201cMy\nson?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 27:2"}, "He said, \u201cSee now, I am old. I don\u2019t know the day of my death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 27:3"}, "Now therefore, please take your weapons, your quiver and your bow, and go out to the field, and get me venison.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 27:4"}, "Make me savoury food, such as I love, and bring it to me, that I may eat, and that my soul may bless you before I die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 27:5"}, "Rebekah heard when Is\u1e25\u0101q spoke to Esau his son. Esau went to the field to hunt for venison, and to bring it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 27:6"}, "Rebekah spoke to Yaqub her son, saying, \u201cBehold, I heard your father speak to Esau your brother, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 27:7"}, "\u2018Bring me venison, and make me savoury food, that I may eat, and bless you before the LORD before my death.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 27:8"}, "Now therefore, my son, obey my voice according to that which I command you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 27:9"}, "Go now to the flock and get me two good young goats from there. I will make them savoury food for your father, such as he\nloves. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 27:10"}, "You shall bring it to your father, that he may eat, so that he may bless you before his death.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 27:11"}, "Yaqub said to Rebekah his mother, \u201cBehold, Esau my brother is a hairy man, and I am a smooth man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 27:12"}, "What if my father touches me? I will seem to him as a deceiver, and I would bring a curse on myself, and not a blessing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 27:13"}, "His mother said to him, \u201cLet your curse be on me, my son. Only obey my voice, and go get them for me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 27:14"}, "He went, and got them, and brought them to his mother. His mother made savoury food, such as his father loved.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 27:15"}, "Rebekah took the good clothes of Esau, her elder son, which were with her in the house, and put them on Yaqub, her\nyounger son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 27:16"}, "She put the skins of the young goats on his hands, and on the smooth of his neck.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 27:17"}, "She gave the savoury food and the bread, which she had prepared, into the hand of her son Yaqub.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 27:18"}, "He came to his father, and said, \u201cMy father?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am. Who are you, my son?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 27:19"}, "Yaqub said to his father, \u201cI am Esau your firstborn. I have done what you asked me to do. Please arise, sit and eat of my\nvenison, that your soul may bless me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 27:20"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q said to his son, \u201cHow is it that you have found it so quickly, my son?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cBecause Allah your LORD gave me success.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 27:21"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q said to Yaqub, \u201cPlease come near, that I may feel you, my son, whether you are really my son Esau or not.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 27:22"}, "Yaqub went near to Is\u1e25\u0101q his father. He felt him, and said, \u201cThe voice is Yaqub\u2019s voice, but the hands are the hands of\nEsau.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 27:23"}, "He didn\u2019t recognise him, because his hands were hairy, like his brother, Esau\u2019s hands. So he blessed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 27:24"}, "He said, \u201cAre you really my son Esau?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 27:25"}, "He said, \u201cBring it near to me, and I will eat of my son\u2019s venison, that my soul may bless you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He brought it near to him, and he ate. He brought him wine, and he drank.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 27:26"}, "His father Is\u1e25\u0101q said to him, \u201cCome near now, and kiss me, my son.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 27:27"}, "He came near, and kissed him. He smelled the smell of his clothing, and blessed him, and said,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold, the smell of my son \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["is as the smell of a field which the LORD has blessed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 27:28"}, "Allah give you of the dew of the sky, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["of the fatness of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and plenty of grain and new wine. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 27:29"}, "Let peoples serve you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and nations bow down to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Be lord over your brothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let your mother\u2019s sons bow down to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Cursed be everyone who curses you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Blessed be everyone who blesses you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 27:30"}, "As soon as Is\u1e25\u0101q had finished blessing Yaqub, and Yaqub had just gone out from the presence of Is\u1e25\u0101q his father, Esau his\nbrother came in from his hunting. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 27:31"}, "He also made savoury food, and brought it to his father. He said to his father, \u201cLet my father arise, and eat of his\nson\u2019s venison, that your soul may bless me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 27:32"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q his father said to him, \u201cWho are you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cI am your son, your firstborn, Esau.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 27:33"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q trembled violently, and said, \u201cWho, then, is he who has taken venison, and brought it to me, and I have eaten of\nall before you came, and have blessed him? Yes, he will be blessed.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 27:34"}, "When Esau heard the words of his father, he cried with an exceedingly great and bitter cry, and said to his father,\n\u201cBless me, even me also, my father.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 27:35"}, "He said, \u201cYour brother came with deceit, and has taken away your blessing.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 27:36"}, "He said, \u201cIsn\u2019t he rightly named Yaqub? For he has supplanted me these two times. He took away my birthright. See, now he\nhas taken away my blessing.\u201d He said, \u201cHaven\u2019t you reserved a blessing for me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 27:37"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q answered Esau, \u201cBehold, I have made him your lord, and all his brothers I have given to him for servants. I have\nsustained him with grain and new wine. What then will I do for you, my son?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 27:38"}, "Esau said to his father, \u201cDo you have just one blessing, my father? Bless me, even me also, my father.\u201d Esau lifted up\nhis voice, and wept. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 27:39"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q his father answered him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold, your dwelling will be of the fatness of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and of the dew of the sky from above. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 27:40"}, "You will live by your sword, and you will serve your brother.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["It will happen, when you will break loose, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that you will shake his yoke from off your neck.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 27:41"}, "Esau hated Yaqub because of the blessing with which his father blessed him. Esau said in his heart, \u201cThe days of mourning\nfor my father are at hand. Then I will kill my brother Yaqub.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 27:42"}, "The words of Esau, her elder son, were told to Rebekah. She sent and called Yaqub, her younger son, and said to him,\n\u201cBehold, your brother Esau comforts himself about you by planning to kill you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 27:43"}, "Now therefore, my son, obey my voice. Arise, flee to Laban, my brother, in Haran.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "GEN 27:44"}, "Stay with him a few days, until your brother\u2019s fury turns away\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "GEN 27:45"}, "until your brother\u2019s anger turns away from you, and he forgets what you have done to him. Then I will send, and get you\nfrom there. Why should I be bereaved of you both in one day?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "GEN 27:46"}, "Rebekah said to Is\u1e25\u0101q, \u201cI am weary of my life because of the daughters of Heth. If Yaqub takes a wife of the daughters of\nHeth, such as these, of the daughters of the land, what good will my life do me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 28:1"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q called Yaqub, blessed him, and commanded him, \u201cYou shall not take a wife of the daughters of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 28:2"}, "Arise, go to Paddan Aram, to the house of Bethuel your mother\u2019s father. Take a wife from there from the daughters of\nLaban, your mother\u2019s brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 28:3"}, "May Allah Ta\u2019ala bless you, and make you fruitful, and multiply you, that you may be a company of peoples,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 28:4"}, "and give you the blessing of Ibrahim, to you and to your offspring with you, that you may inherit the land where you\ntravel, which Allah gave to Ibrahim.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 28:5"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q sent Yaqub away. He went to Paddan Aram to Laban, son of Bethuel the Syrian, the brother of Rebekah, Yaqub\u2019s and\nEsau\u2019s mother. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 28:6"}, "Now Esau saw that Is\u1e25\u0101q had blessed Yaqub and sent him away to Paddan Aram, to take him a wife from there, and that as he\nblessed him he gave him a command, saying, \u201cYou shall not take a wife of the daughters of Canaan;\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 28:7"}, "and that Yaqub obeyed his father and his mother, and was gone to Paddan Aram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 28:8"}, "Esau saw that the daughters of Canaan didn\u2019t please Is\u1e25\u0101q, his father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 28:9"}, "Esau went to Ismail, and took, in addition to the wives that he had, Mahalath the daughter of Ismail, Ibrahim\u2019s son, the\nsister of Nebaioth, to be his wife. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 28:10"}, "Yaqub went out from Beersheba, and went towards Haran. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 28:11"}, "He came to a certain place, and stayed there all night, because the sun had set. He took one of the stones of the place,\nand put it under his head, and lay down in that place to sleep. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 28:12"}, "He dreamt and saw a stairway set upon the earth, and its top reached to heaven. Behold, the angels of Allah were\nascending and descending on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 28:13"}, "Behold, the LORD stood above it, and said, \u201cI am the LORD, Allah of Ibrahim your father, and Allah of Is\u1e25\u0101q. I will give\nthe land you lie on to you and to your offspring. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 28:14"}, "Your offspring will be as the dust of the earth, and you will spread abroad to the west, and to the east, and to the\nnorth, and to the south. In you and in your offspring, all the families of the earth will be blessed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 28:15"}, "Behold, I am with you, and will keep you, wherever you go, and will bring you again into this land. For I will not leave\nyou, until I have done that which I have spoken of to you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 28:16"}, "Yaqub awakened out of his sleep, and he said, \u201cSurely the LORD is in this place, and I didn\u2019t know it.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 28:17"}, "He was afraid, and said, \u201cHow awesome this place is! This is none other than Allah\u2019s house, and this is the gate of\nheaven.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 28:18"}, "Yaqub rose up early in the morning, and took the stone that he had put under his head, and set it up for a pillar, and\npoured oil on its top. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 28:19"}, "He called the name of that place Bethel, but the name of the city was Luz at the first.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 28:20"}, "Yaqub vowed a vow, saying, \u201cIf Allah will be with me, and will keep me in this way that I go, and will give me bread to\neat, and clothing to put on, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 28:21"}, "so that I come again to my father\u2019s house in peace, and the LORD will be my Allah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 28:22"}, "then this stone, which I have set up for a pillar, will be Allah\u2019s house. Of all that you will give me I will surely give\na tenth to you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 29:1"}, "Then Yaqub went on his journey, and came to the land of the children of the east.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 29:2"}, "He looked, and behold, a well in the field, and saw three flocks of sheep lying there by it. For out of that well they\nwatered the flocks. The stone on the well\u2019s mouth was large. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 29:3"}, "There all the flocks were gathered. They rolled the stone from the well\u2019s mouth, and watered the sheep, and put the stone\nagain on the well\u2019s mouth in its place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 29:4"}, "Yaqub said to them, \u201cMy relatives, where are you from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cWe are from Haran.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 29:5"}, "He said to them, \u201cDo you know Laban, the son of Nahor?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cWe know him.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 29:6"}, "He said to them, \u201cIs it well with him?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cIt is well. See, Rachel, his daughter, is coming with the sheep.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 29:7"}, "He said, \u201cBehold, it is still the middle of the day, not time to gather the livestock together. Water the sheep, and go\nand feed them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 29:8"}, "They said, \u201cWe can\u2019t, until all the flocks are gathered together, and they roll the stone from the well\u2019s mouth. Then we\nwater the sheep.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 29:9"}, "While he was yet speaking with them, Rachel came with her father\u2019s sheep, for she kept them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 29:10"}, "When Yaqub saw Rachel the daughter of Laban, his mother\u2019s brother, and the sheep of Laban, his mother\u2019s brother, Yaqub\nwent near, and rolled the stone from the well\u2019s mouth, and watered the flock of Laban his mother\u2019s brother.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 29:11"}, "Yaqub kissed Rachel, and lifted up his voice, and wept. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 29:12"}, "Yaqub told Rachel that he was her father\u2019s relative, and that he was Rebekah\u2019s son. She ran and told her father.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 29:13"}, "When Laban heard the news of Yaqub, his sister\u2019s son, he ran to meet Yaqub, and embraced him, and kissed him, and brought\nhim to his house. Yaqub told Laban all these things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 29:14"}, "Laban said to him, \u201cSurely you are my bone and my flesh.\u201d Yaqub stayed with him for a month.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 29:15"}, "Laban said to Yaqub, \u201cBecause you are my relative, should you therefore serve me for nothing? Tell me, what will your\nwages be?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 29:16"}, "Laban had two daughters. The name of the elder was Leah, and the name of the younger was Rachel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 29:17"}, "Leah\u2019s eyes were weak, but Rachel was beautiful in form and attractive.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 29:18"}, "Yaqub loved Rachel. He said, \u201cI will serve you seven years for Rachel, your younger daughter.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 29:19"}, "Laban said, \u201cIt is better that I give her to you, than that I should give her to another man. Stay with me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 29:20"}, "Yaqub served seven years for Rachel. They seemed to him but a few days, for the love he had for her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 29:21"}, "Yaqub said to Laban, \u201cGive me my wife, for my days are fulfilled, that I may go in to her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 29:22"}, "Laban gathered together all the men of the place, and made a feast.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 29:23"}, "In the evening, he took Leah his daughter, and brought her to Yaqub. He went in to her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 29:24"}, "Laban gave Zilpah his servant to his daughter Leah for a servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 29:25"}, "In the morning, behold, it was Leah! He said to Laban, \u201cWhat is this you have done to me? Didn\u2019t I serve with you for\nRachel? Why then have you deceived me?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 29:26"}, "Laban said, \u201cIt is not done so in our place, to give the younger before the firstborn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 29:27"}, "Fulfil the week of this one, and we will give you the other also for the service which you will serve with me for seven\nmore years.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 29:28"}, "Yaqub did so, and fulfilled her week. He gave him Rachel his daughter as wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 29:29"}, "Laban gave Bilhah, his servant, to his daughter Rachel to be her servant.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 29:30"}, "He went in also to Rachel, and he loved also Rachel more than Leah, and served with him seven more years.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 29:31"}, "The LORD saw that Leah was hated, and he opened her womb, but Rachel was barren.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 29:32"}, "Leah conceived, and bore a son, and she named him Reuben. For she said, \u201cBecause the LORD has looked at my affliction;\nfor now my husband will love me.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 29:33"}, "She conceived again, and bore a son, and said, \u201cBecause the LORD has heard that I am hated, he has therefore given me\nthis son also.\u201d She named him Simeon. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 29:34"}, "She conceived again, and bore a son. She said, \u201cNow this time my husband will be joined to me, because I have borne him\nthree sons.\u201d Therefore his name was called Levi. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 29:35"}, "She conceived again, and bore a son. She said, \u201cThis time I will praise the LORD.\u201d Therefore she named him Judah. Then\nshe stopped bearing. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 30"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 30:1"}, "When Rachel saw that she bore Yaqub no children, Rachel envied her sister. She said to Yaqub, \u201cGive me children, or else I\nwill die.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 30:2"}, "Yaqub\u2019s anger burnt against Rachel, and he said, \u201cAm I in Allah\u2019s place, who has withheld from you the fruit of the womb?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 30:3"}, "She said, \u201cBehold, my maid Bilhah. Go in to her, that she may bear on my knees, and I also may obtain children by her.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 30:4"}, "She gave him Bilhah her servant as wife, and Yaqub went in to her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 30:5"}, "Bilhah conceived, and bore Yaqub a son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 30:6"}, "Rachel said, \u201cAllah has judged me, and has also heard my voice, and has given me a son.\u201d Therefore she called his name\nDan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 30:7"}, "Bilhah, Rachel\u2019s servant, conceived again, and bore Yaqub a second son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 30:8"}, "Rachel said, \u201cI have wrestled with my sister with mighty wrestlings, and have prevailed.\u201d She named him Naphtali.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 30:9"}, "When Leah saw that she had finished bearing, she took Zilpah, her servant, and gave her to Yaqub as a wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 30:10"}, "Zilpah, Leah\u2019s servant, bore Yaqub a son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 30:11"}, "Leah said, \u201cHow fortunate!\u201d She named him Gad. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 30:12"}, "Zilpah, Leah\u2019s servant, bore Yaqub a second son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 30:13"}, "Leah said, \u201cHappy am I, for the daughters will call me happy.\u201d She named him Asher.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 30:14"}, "Reuben went in the days of wheat harvest, and found mandrakes in the field, and brought them to his mother, Leah. Then\nRachel said to Leah, \u201cPlease give me some of your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 30:15"}, "Leah said to her, \u201cIs it a small matter that you have taken away my husband? Would you take away my son\u2019s mandrakes,\nalso?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Rachel said, \u201cTherefore he will lie with you tonight for your son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 30:16"}, "Yaqub came from the field in the evening, and Leah went out to meet him, and said, \u201cYou must come in to me; for I have\nsurely hired you with my son\u2019s mandrakes.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He lay with her that night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 30:17"}, "Allah listened to Leah, and she conceived, and bore Yaqub a fifth son.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 30:18"}, "Leah said, \u201cAllah has given me my hire, because I gave my servant to my husband.\u201d She named him Issachar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 30:19"}, "Leah conceived again, and bore a sixth son to Yaqub. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 30:20"}, "Leah said, \u201cAllah has endowed me with a good dowry. Now my husband will live with me, because I have borne him six sons.\u201d\nShe named him Zebulun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 30:21"}, "Afterwards, she bore a daughter, and named her Dinah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 30:22"}, "Allah remembered Rachel, and Allah listened to her, and opened her womb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 30:23"}, "She conceived, bore a son, and said, \u201cAllah has taken away my reproach.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 30:24"}, "She named him Yusuf,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["30:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Yusuf means \u201cmay he\nadd\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " saying, \u201cMay the LORD add another son to me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 30:25"}, "When Rachel had borne Yusuf, Yaqub said to Laban, \u201cSend me away, that I may go to my own place, and to my country.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 30:26"}, "Give me my wives and my children for whom I have served you, and let me go; for you know my service with which I have\nserved you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 30:27"}, "Laban said to him, \u201cIf now I have found favour in your eyes, stay here, for I have divined that the LORD has blessed me\nfor your sake.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 30:28"}, "He said, \u201cAppoint me your wages, and I will give it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 30:29"}, "Yaqub said to him, \u201cYou know how I have served you, and how your livestock have fared with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 30:30"}, "For it was little which you had before I came, and it has increased to a multitude. The LORD has blessed you wherever I\nturned. Now when will I provide for my own house also?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 30:31"}, "Laban said, \u201cWhat shall I give you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yaqub said, \u201cYou shall not give me anything. If you will do this thing for me, I will again feed your flock and keep it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 30:32"}, "I will pass through all your flock today, removing from there every speckled and spotted one, and every black one amongst\nthe sheep, and the spotted and speckled amongst the goats. This will be my hire.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 30:33"}, "So my righteousness will answer for me hereafter, when you come concerning my hire that is before you. Every one that is\nnot speckled and spotted amongst the goats, and black amongst the sheep, that might be with me, will be considered stolen.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 30:34"}, "Laban said, \u201cBehold, let it be according to your word.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 30:35"}, "That day, he removed the male goats that were streaked and spotted, and all the female goats that were speckled and\nspotted, every one that had white in it, and all the black ones amongst the sheep, and gave them into the hand of his sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 30:36"}, "He set three days\u2019 journey between himself and Yaqub, and Yaqub fed the rest of Laban\u2019s flocks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 30:37"}, "Yaqub took to himself rods of fresh poplar, almond, and plane tree, peeled white streaks in them, and made the white\nappear which was in the rods. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 30:38"}, "He set the rods which he had peeled opposite the flocks in the watering troughs where the flocks came to drink. They\nconceived when they came to drink. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 30:39"}, "The flocks conceived before the rods, and the flocks produced streaked, speckled, and spotted.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 30:40"}, "Yaqub separated the lambs, and set the faces of the flocks towards the streaked and all the black in Laban\u2019s flock. He\nput his own droves apart, and didn\u2019t put them into Laban\u2019s flock.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 30:41"}, "Whenever the stronger of the flock conceived, Yaqub laid the rods in front of the eyes of the flock in the watering\ntroughs, that they might conceive amongst the rods; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 30:42"}, "but when the flock were feeble, he didn\u2019t put them in. So the feebler were Laban\u2019s, and the stronger Yaqub\u2019s.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 30:43"}, "The man increased exceedingly, and had large flocks, female servants and male servants, and camels and donkeys.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 31"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 31:1"}, "Yaqub heard Laban\u2019s sons\u2019 words, saying, \u201cYaqub has taken away all that was our father\u2019s. He has obtained all this wealth\nfrom that which was our father\u2019s.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 31:2"}, "Yaqub saw the expression on Laban\u2019s face, and, behold, it was not towards him as before.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 31:3"}, "The LORD said to Yaqub, \u201cReturn to the land of your fathers, and to your relatives, and I will be with you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 31:4"}, "Yaqub sent and called Rachel and Leah to the field to his flock,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 31:5"}, "and said to them, \u201cI see the expression on your father\u2019s face, that it is not towards me as before; but Allah of my father\nhas been with me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 31:6"}, "You know that I have served your father with all of my strength.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 31:7"}, "Your father has deceived me, and changed my wages ten times, but Allah didn\u2019t allow him to hurt me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 31:8"}, "If he said, \u2018The speckled will be your wages,\u2019 then all the flock bore speckled. If he said, \u2018The streaked will be your\nwages,\u2019 then all the flock bore streaked. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 31:9"}, "Thus Allah has taken away your father\u2019s livestock, and given them to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 31:10"}, "During mating season, I lifted up my eyes, and saw in a dream, and behold, the male goats which leapt on the flock were\nstreaked, speckled, and grizzled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 31:11"}, "The angel of Allah said to me in the dream, \u2018Yaqub,\u2019 and I said, \u2018Here I am.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 31:12"}, "He said, \u2018Now lift up your eyes, and behold, all the male goats which leap on the flock are streaked, speckled, and\ngrizzled, for I have seen all that Laban does to you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 31:13"}, "I am Allah of Bethel, where you anointed a pillar, where you vowed a vow to me. Now arise, get out from this land, and\nreturn to the land of your birth.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 31:14"}, "Rachel and Leah answered him, \u201cIs there yet any portion or inheritance for us in our father\u2019s house?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 31:15"}, "Aren\u2019t we considered as foreigners by him? For he has sold us, and has also used up our money.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 31:16"}, "For all the riches which Allah has taken away from our father are ours and our children\u2019s. Now then, whatever Allah has\nsaid to you, do.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 31:17"}, "Then Yaqub rose up, and set his sons and his wives on the camels,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 31:18"}, "and he took away all his livestock, and all his possessions which he had gathered, including the livestock which he had\ngained in Paddan Aram, to go to Is\u1e25\u0101q his father, to the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 31:19"}, "Now Laban had gone to shear his sheep; and Rachel stole the teraphim\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["31:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with inheritance rights to the household\nproperty."]}], "caller": "+"}, " that were her father\u2019s. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 31:20"}, "Yaqub deceived Laban the Syrian, in that he didn\u2019t tell him that he was running away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 31:21"}, "So he fled with all that he had. He rose up, passed over the River, and set his face towards the mountain of Gilead.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 31:22"}, "Laban was told on the third day that Yaqub had fled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 31:23"}, "He took his relatives with him, and pursued him seven days\u2019 journey. He overtook him in the mountain of Gilead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 31:24"}, "Allah came to Laban the Syrian in a dream of the night, and said to him, \u201cBe careful that you don\u2019t speak to Yaqub either\ngood or bad.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 31:25"}, "Laban caught up with Yaqub. Now Yaqub had pitched his tent in the mountain, and Laban with his relatives encamped in the\nmountain of Gilead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 31:26"}, "Laban said to Yaqub, \u201cWhat have you done, that you have deceived me, and carried away my daughters like captives of the\nsword? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 31:27"}, "Why did you flee secretly, and deceive me, and didn\u2019t tell me, that I might have sent you away with mirth and with songs,\nwith tambourine and with harp; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 31:28"}, "and didn\u2019t allow me to kiss my sons and my daughters? Now have you done foolishly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 31:29"}, "It is in the power of my hand to hurt you, but Allah of your father spoke to me last night, saying, \u2018Be careful that you\ndon\u2019t speak to Yaqub either good or bad.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 31:30"}, "Now, you want to be gone, because you greatly longed for your father\u2019s house, but why have you stolen my gods?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 31:31"}, "Yaqub answered Laban, \u201cBecause I was afraid, for I said, \u2018Lest you should take your daughters from me by force.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 31:32"}, "Anyone you find your gods with shall not live. Before our relatives, discern what is yours with me, and take it.\u201d For\nYaqub didn\u2019t know that Rachel had stolen them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 31:33"}, "Laban went into Yaqub\u2019s tent, into Leah\u2019s tent, and into the tent of the two female servants; but he didn\u2019t find them. He\nwent out of Leah\u2019s tent, and entered into Rachel\u2019s tent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 31:34"}, "Now Rachel had taken the teraphim, put them in the camel\u2019s saddle, and sat on them. Laban felt around all the tent, but\ndidn\u2019t find them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 31:35"}, "She said to her father, \u201cDon\u2019t let my lord be angry that I can\u2019t rise up before you; for I\u2019m having my period.\u201d He\nsearched, but didn\u2019t find the teraphim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 31:36"}, "Yaqub was angry, and argued with Laban. Yaqub answered Laban, \u201cWhat is my trespass? What is my sin, that you have hotly\npursued me? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 31:37"}, "Now that you have felt around in all my stuff, what have you found of all your household stuff? Set it here before my\nrelatives and your relatives, that they may judge between us two.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 31:38"}, "\u201cThese twenty years I have been with you. Your ewes and your female goats have not cast their young, and I haven\u2019t eaten\nthe rams of your flocks. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 31:39"}, "That which was torn of animals, I didn\u2019t bring to you. I bore its loss. Of my hand you required it, whether stolen by day\nor stolen by night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 31:40"}, "This was my situation: in the day the drought consumed me, and the frost by night; and my sleep fled from my eyes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 31:41"}, "These twenty years I have been in your house. I served you fourteen years for your two daughters, and six years for your\nflock, and you have changed my wages ten times. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 31:42"}, "Unless Allah of my father, Allah of Ibrahim, and the fear of Is\u1e25\u0101q, had been with me, surely now you would have sent me\naway empty. Allah has seen my affliction and the labour of my hands, and rebuked you last night.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 31:43"}, "Laban answered Yaqub, \u201cThe daughters are my daughters, the children are my children, the flocks are my flocks, and all\nthat you see is mine! What can I do today to these my daughters, or to their children whom they have borne?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "GEN 31:44"}, "Now come, let\u2019s make a covenant, you and I. Let it be for a witness between me and you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "GEN 31:45"}, "Yaqub took a stone, and set it up for a pillar. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "GEN 31:46"}, "Yaqub said to his relatives, \u201cGather stones.\u201d They took stones, and made a heap. They ate there by the heap.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "GEN 31:47"}, "Laban called it Jegar Sahadutha,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["31:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cJegar Sahadutha\u201d means \u201cWitness Heap\u201d in\nAramaic."]}], "caller": "+"}, " but Yaqub called it Galeed.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["31:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cGaleed\u201d means \u201cWitness Heap\u201d in\nHebrew."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "GEN 31:48"}, "Laban said, \u201cThis heap is witness between me and you today.\u201d Therefore it was named Galeed\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "GEN 31:49"}, "and Mizpah, for he said, \u201cThe LORD watch between me and you, when we are absent one from another.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "GEN 31:50"}, "If you afflict my daughters, or if you take wives in addition to my daughters, no man is with us; behold, Allah is\nwitness between me and you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "GEN 31:51"}, "Laban said to Yaqub, \u201cSee this heap, and see the pillar, which I have set between me and you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "GEN 31:52"}, "May this heap be a witness, and the pillar be a witness, that I will not pass over this heap to you, and that you will\nnot pass over this heap and this pillar to me, for harm. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "GEN 31:53"}, "The Allah of Ibrahim, and Allah of Nahor, Allah of their father, judge between us.\u201d Then Yaqub swore by the fear of his\nfather, Is\u1e25\u0101q. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "GEN 31:54"}, "Yaqub offered a sacrifice in the mountain, and called his relatives to eat bread. They ate bread, and stayed all night in\nthe mountain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "GEN 31:55"}, "Early in the morning, Laban rose up, and kissed his sons and his daughters, and blessed them. Laban departed and returned\nto his place. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 32"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 32:1"}, "Yaqub went on his way, and the angels of Allah met him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 32:2"}, "When he saw them, Yaqub said, \u201cThis is Allah\u2019s army.\u201d He called the name of that place Mahanaim.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 32:3"}, "Yaqub sent messengers in front of him to Esau, his brother, to the land of Seir, the field of Edom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 32:4"}, "He commanded them, saying, \u201cThis is what you shall tell my lord, Esau: \u2018This is what your servant, Yaqub, says. I have\nlived as a foreigner with Laban, and stayed until now. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 32:5"}, "I have cattle, donkeys, flocks, male servants, and female servants. I have sent to tell my lord, that I may find favour in\nyour sight.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 32:6"}, "The messengers returned to Yaqub, saying, \u201cWe came to your brother Esau. He is coming to meet you, and four hundred men\nare with him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 32:7"}, "Then Yaqub was greatly afraid and was distressed. He divided the people who were with him, and the flocks, and the herds,\nand the camels, into two companies; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 32:8"}, "and he said, \u201cIf Esau comes to the one company, and strikes it, then the company which is left will escape.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 32:9"}, "Yaqub said, \u201cAllah of my father Ibrahim, and Allah of my father Is\u1e25\u0101q, the LORD, who said to me, \u2018Return to your country,\nand to your relatives, and I will do you good,\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 32:10"}, "I am not worthy of the least of all the loving kindnesses, and of all the truth, which you have shown to your servant;\nfor with just my staff I crossed over this Jordan; and now I have become two companies.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 32:11"}, "Please deliver me from the hand of my brother, from the hand of Esau; for I fear him, lest he come and strike me and the\nmothers with the children. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 32:12"}, "You said, \u2018I will surely do you good, and make your offspring as the sand of the sea, which can\u2019t be counted because\nthere are so many.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 32:13"}, "He stayed there that night, and took from that which he had with him a present for Esau, his brother:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 32:14"}, "two hundred female goats and twenty male goats, two hundred ewes and twenty rams,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 32:15"}, "thirty milk camels and their colts, forty cows, ten bulls, twenty female donkeys and ten foals.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 32:16"}, "He delivered them into the hands of his servants, every herd by itself, and said to his servants, \u201cPass over before me,\nand put a space between herd and herd.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 32:17"}, "He commanded the foremost, saying, \u201cWhen Esau, my brother, meets you, and asks you, saying, \u2018Whose are you? Where are you\ngoing? Whose are these before you?\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 32:18"}, "Then you shall say, \u2018They are your servant, Yaqub\u2019s. It is a present sent to my lord, Esau. Behold, he also is behind\nus.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 32:19"}, "He commanded also the second, and the third, and all that followed the herds, saying, \u201cThis is how you shall speak to\nEsau, when you find him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 32:20"}, "You shall say, \u2018Not only that, but behold, your servant, Yaqub, is behind us.\u2019\u201d For, he said, \u201cI will appease him with\nthe present that goes before me, and afterward I will see his face. Perhaps he will accept me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 32:21"}, "So the present passed over before him, and he himself stayed that night in the camp.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 32:22"}, "He rose up that night, and took his two wives, and his two servants, and his eleven sons, and crossed over the ford of\nthe Jabbok. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 32:23"}, "He took them, and sent them over the stream, and sent over that which he had.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 32:24"}, "Yaqub was left alone, and wrestled with a man there until the breaking of the day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 32:25"}, "When he saw that he didn\u2019t prevail against him, the man touched the hollow of his thigh, and the hollow of Yaqub\u2019s thigh\nwas strained as he wrestled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 32:26"}, "The man said, \u201cLet me go, for the day breaks.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yaqub said, \u201cI won\u2019t let you go unless you bless me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 32:27"}, "He said to him, \u201cWhat is your name?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cYaqub\u201d. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 32:28"}, "He said, \u201cYour name will no longer be called Yaqub, but Israel; for you have fought with Allah and with men, and have\nprevailed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 32:29"}, "Yaqub asked him, \u201cPlease tell me your name.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cWhy is it that you ask what my name is?\u201d He blessed him there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 32:30"}, "Yaqub called the name of the place Peniel;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["32:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Peniel means \u201cface of\nAllah\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " for he said, \u201cI have seen Allah face to face, and my life is preserved.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 32:31"}, "The sun rose on him as he passed over Peniel, and he limped because of his thigh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 32:32"}, "Therefore the children of Israel don\u2019t eat the sinew of the hip, which is on the hollow of the thigh, to this day,\nbecause he touched the hollow of Yaqub\u2019s thigh in the sinew of the hip.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 33"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 33:1"}, "Yaqub lifted up his eyes, and looked, and, behold, Esau was coming, and with him four hundred men. He divided the children\nbetween Leah, Rachel, and the two servants. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 33:2"}, "He put the servants and their children in front, Leah and her children after, and Rachel and Yusuf at the rear.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 33:3"}, "He himself passed over in front of them, and bowed himself to the ground seven times, until he came near to his brother.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 33:4"}, "Esau ran to meet him, embraced him, fell on his neck, kissed him, and they wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 33:5"}, "He lifted up his eyes, and saw the women and the children; and said, \u201cWho are these with you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cThe children whom Allah has graciously given your servant.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 33:6"}, "Then the servants came near with their children, and they bowed themselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 33:7"}, "Leah also and her children came near, and bowed themselves. After them, Yusuf came near with Rachel, and they bowed\nthemselves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 33:8"}, "Esau said, \u201cWhat do you mean by all this company which I met?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yaqub said, \u201cTo find favour in the sight of my lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 33:9"}, "Esau said, \u201cI have enough, my brother; let that which you have be yours.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 33:10"}, "Yaqub said, \u201cPlease, no, if I have now found favour in your sight, then receive my present at my hand, because I have\nseen your face, as one sees the face of Allah, and you were pleased with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 33:11"}, "Please take the gift that I brought to you, because Allah has dealt graciously with me, and because I have enough.\u201d He\nurged him, and he took it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 33:12"}, "Esau said, \u201cLet\u2019s take our journey, and let\u2019s go, and I will go before you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 33:13"}, "Yaqub said to him, \u201cMy lord knows that the children are tender, and that the flocks and herds with me have their young,\nand if they overdrive them one day, all the flocks will die. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 33:14"}, "Please let my lord pass over before his servant, and I will lead on gently, according to the pace of the livestock that\nare before me and according to the pace of the children, until I come to my lord to Seir.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 33:15"}, "Esau said, \u201cLet me now leave with you some of the people who are with me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cWhy? Let me find favour in the sight of my lord.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 33:16"}, "So Esau returned that day on his way to Seir. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 33:17"}, "Yaqub travelled to Succoth, built himself a house, and made shelters for his livestock. Therefore the name of the place\nis called Succoth.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["33:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["succoth means shelters or booths."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 33:18"}, "Yaqub came in peace to the city of Shechem, which is in the land of Canaan, when he came from Paddan Aram; and encamped\nbefore the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 33:19"}, "He bought the parcel of ground where he had spread his tent, at the hand of the children of Hamor, Shechem\u2019s father, for\none hundred pieces of money. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 33:20"}, "He erected an altar there, and called it El Elohe Israel.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["33:20 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["El Elohe Israel means \u201cAllah, Allah of Israel\u201d or \u201cThe Allah of Israel is mighty\u201d.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 34"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 34:1"}, "Dinah, the daughter of Leah, whom she bore to Yaqub, went out to see the daughters of the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 34:2"}, "Shechem the son of Hamor the Hivite, the prince of the land, saw her. He took her, lay with her, and humbled her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 34:3"}, "His soul joined to Dinah, the daughter of Yaqub, and he loved the young lady, and spoke kindly to the young lady.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 34:4"}, "Shechem spoke to his father, Hamor, saying, \u201cGet me this young lady as a wife.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 34:5"}, "Now Yaqub heard that he had defiled Dinah, his daughter; and his sons were with his livestock in the field. Yaqub held his\npeace until they came. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 34:6"}, "Hamor the father of Shechem went out to Yaqub to talk with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 34:7"}, "The sons of Yaqub came in from the field when they heard it. The men were grieved, and they were very angry, because he\nhad done folly in Israel in lying with Yaqub\u2019s daughter, a thing ought not to be done.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 34:8"}, "Hamor talked with them, saying, \u201cThe soul of my son, Shechem, longs for your daughter. Please give her to him as a wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 34:9"}, "Make marriages with us. Give your daughters to us, and take our daughters for yourselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 34:10"}, "You shall dwell with us, and the land will be before you. Live and trade in it, and get possessions in it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 34:11"}, "Shechem said to her father and to her brothers, \u201cLet me find favour in your eyes, and whatever you will tell me I will\ngive. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 34:12"}, "Ask me a great amount for a dowry, and I will give whatever you ask of me, but give me the young lady as a wife.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 34:13"}, "The sons of Yaqub answered Shechem and Hamor his father with deceit when they spoke, because he had defiled Dinah their\nsister, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 34:14"}, "and said to them, \u201cWe can\u2019t do this thing, to give our sister to one who is uncircumcised; for that is a reproach to us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 34:15"}, "Only on this condition will we consent to you. If you will be as we are, that every male of you be circumcised,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 34:16"}, "then will we give our daughters to you; and we will take your daughters to us, and we will dwell with you, and we will\nbecome one people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 34:17"}, "But if you will not listen to us and be circumcised, then we will take our\nsister,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["34:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Hebrew has, literally, \u201cdaughter\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and we will be gone.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 34:18"}, "Their words pleased Hamor and Shechem, Hamor\u2019s son. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 34:19"}, "The young man didn\u2019t wait to do this thing, because he had delight in Yaqub\u2019s daughter, and he was honoured above all the\nhouse of his father. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 34:20"}, "Hamor and Shechem, his son, came to the gate of their city, and talked with the men of their city, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 34:21"}, "\u201cThese men are peaceful with us. Therefore let them live in the land and trade in it. For behold, the land is large\nenough for them. Let\u2019s take their daughters to us for wives, and let\u2019s give them our daughters.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 34:22"}, "Only on this condition will the men consent to us to live with us, to become one people, if every male amongst us is\ncircumcised, as they are circumcised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 34:23"}, "Won\u2019t their livestock and their possessions and all their animals be ours? Only let\u2019s give our consent to them, and they\nwill dwell with us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 34:24"}, "All who went out of the gate of his city listened to Hamor, and to Shechem his son; and every male was circumcised, all\nwho went out of the gate of his city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 34:25"}, "On the third day, when they were sore, two of Yaqub\u2019s sons, Simeon and Levi, Dinah\u2019s brothers, each took his sword, came\nupon the unsuspecting city, and killed all the males. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 34:26"}, "They killed Hamor and Shechem, his son, with the edge of the sword, and took Dinah out of Shechem\u2019s house, and went away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 34:27"}, "Yaqub\u2019s sons came on the dead, and plundered the city, because they had defiled their sister.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 34:28"}, "They took their flocks, their herds, their donkeys, that which was in the city, that which was in the field,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 34:29"}, "and all their wealth. They took captive all their little ones and their wives, and took as plunder everything that was in\nthe house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 34:30"}, "Yaqub said to Simeon and Levi, \u201cYou have troubled me, to make me odious to the inhabitants of the land, amongst the\nCanaanites and the Perizzites. I am few in number. They will gather themselves together against me and strike me, and I will be\ndestroyed, I and my house.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 34:31"}, "They said, \u201cShould he deal with our sister as with a prostitute?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 35"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 35:1"}, "Allah said to Yaqub, \u201cArise, go up to Bethel, and live there. Make there an altar to Allah, who appeared to you when you\nfled from the face of Esau your brother.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 35:2"}, "Then Yaqub said to his household, and to all who were with him, \u201cPut away the foreign gods that are amongst you, purify\nyourselves, change your garments. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 35:3"}, "Let\u2019s arise, and go up to Bethel. I will make there an altar to Allah, who answered me in the day of my distress, and was\nwith me on the way which I went.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 35:4"}, "They gave to Yaqub all the foreign gods which were in their hands, and the rings which were in their ears; and Yaqub hid\nthem under the oak which was by Shechem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 35:5"}, "They travelled, and a terror of Allah was on the cities that were around them, and they didn\u2019t pursue the sons of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 35:6"}, "So Yaqub came to Luz (that is, Bethel), which is in the land of Canaan, he and all the people who were with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 35:7"}, "He built an altar there, and called the place El Beth El; because there Allah was revealed to him, when he fled from the\nface of his brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 35:8"}, "Deborah, Rebekah\u2019s nurse, died, and she was buried below Bethel under the oak; and its name was called Allon Bacuth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 35:9"}, "Allah appeared to Yaqub again, when he came from Paddan Aram, and blessed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 35:10"}, "Allah said to him, \u201cYour name is Yaqub. Your name shall not be Yaqub any more, but your name will be Israel.\u201d He named\nhim Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 35:11"}, "Allah said to him, \u201cI am Allah Ta\u2019ala. Be fruitful and multiply. A nation and a company of nations will be from you, and\nkings will come out of your body. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 35:12"}, "The land which I gave to Ibrahim and Is\u1e25\u0101q, I will give it to you, and to your offspring after you I will give the land.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 35:13"}, "Allah went up from him in the place where he spoke with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 35:14"}, "Yaqub set up a pillar in the place where he spoke with him, a pillar of stone. He poured out a drink offering on it, and\npoured oil on it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 35:15"}, "Yaqub called the name of the place where Allah spoke with him \u201cBethel\u201d.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 35:16"}, "They travelled from Bethel. There was still some distance to come to Ephrath, and Rachel travailed. She had hard labour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 35:17"}, "When she was in hard labour, the midwife said to her, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, for now you will have another son.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 35:18"}, "As her soul was departing (for she died), she named him Benoni,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["35:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBenoni\u201d means \u201cson of my trouble\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " but his father named him\nBenjamin.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["35:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBenjamin\u201d means \u201cson of my right hand\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 35:19"}, "Rachel died, and was buried on the way to Ephrath (also called Bethlehem).\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 35:20"}, "Yaqub set up a pillar on her grave. The same is the Pillar of Rachel\u2019s grave to this day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 35:21"}, "Israel travelled, and spread his tent beyond the tower of Eder.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 35:22"}, "While Israel lived in that land, Reuben went and lay with Bilhah, his father\u2019s concubine, and Israel heard of it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Now the sons of Yaqub were twelve. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 35:23"}, "The sons of Leah: Reuben (Yaqub\u2019s firstborn), Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 35:24"}, "The sons of Rachel: Yusuf and Benjamin. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 35:25"}, "The sons of Bilhah (Rachel\u2019s servant): Dan and Naphtali. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 35:26"}, "The sons of Zilpah (Leah\u2019s servant): Gad and Asher. These are the sons of Yaqub, who were born to him in Paddan Aram.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 35:27"}, "Yaqub came to Is\u1e25\u0101q his father, to Mamre, to Kiriath Arba (which is Hebron), where Ibrahim and Is\u1e25\u0101q lived as foreigners.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 35:28"}, "The days of Is\u1e25\u0101q were one hundred and eighty years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 35:29"}, "Is\u1e25\u0101q gave up the spirit and died, and was gathered to his people, old and full of days. Esau and Yaqub, his sons, buried\nhim. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 36"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 36:1"}, "Now this is the history of the generations of Esau (that is, Edom).\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 36:2"}, "Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter of Elon, the Hittite; and Oholibamah the daughter of\nAnah, the daughter of Zibeon, the Hivite; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 36:3"}, "and Basemath, Ismail\u2019s daughter, sister of Nebaioth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 36:4"}, "Adah bore to Esau Eliphaz. Basemath bore Reuel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 36:5"}, "Oholibamah bore Jeush, Jalam, and Korah. These are the sons of Esau, who were born to him in the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 36:6"}, "Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the members of his household, with his livestock, all his animals,\nand all his possessions, which he had gathered in the land of Canaan, and went into a land away from his brother Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 36:7"}, "For their substance was too great for them to dwell together, and the land of their travels couldn\u2019t bear them because of\ntheir livestock. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 36:8"}, "Esau lived in the hill country of Seir. Esau is Edom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 36:9"}, "This is the history of the generations of Esau the father of the Edomites in the hill country of Seir:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 36:10"}, "these are the names of Esau\u2019s sons: Eliphaz, the son of Adah, the wife of Esau; and Reuel, the son of Basemath, the wife\nof Esau. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 36:11"}, "The sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, and Gatam, and Kenaz.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 36:12"}, "Timna was concubine to Eliphaz, Esau\u2019s son; and she bore to Eliphaz Amalek. These are the descendants of Adah, Esau\u2019s\nwife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 36:13"}, "These are the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the descendants of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 36:14"}, "These were the sons of Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon, Esau\u2019s wife: she bore to Esau Jeush,\nJalam, and Korah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 36:15"}, "These are the chiefs of the sons of Esau: the sons of Eliphaz the firstborn of Esau: chief Teman, chief Omar, chief\nZepho, chief Kenaz, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 36:16"}, "chief Korah, chief Gatam, chief Amalek. These are the chiefs who came of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. These are the sons\nof Adah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 36:17"}, "These are the sons of Reuel, Esau\u2019s son: chief Nahath, chief Zerah, chief Shammah, chief Mizzah. These are the chiefs who\ncame of Reuel in the land of Edom. These are the sons of Basemath, Esau\u2019s wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 36:18"}, "These are the sons of Oholibamah, Esau\u2019s wife: chief Jeush, chief Jalam, chief Korah. These are the chiefs who came of\nOholibamah the daughter of Anah, Esau\u2019s wife. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 36:19"}, "These are the sons of Esau (that is, Edom), and these are their chiefs.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 36:20"}, "These are the sons of Seir the Horite, the inhabitants of the land: Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 36:21"}, "Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These are the chiefs who came of the Horites, the children of Seir in the land of Edom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 36:22"}, "The children of Lotan were Hori and Heman. Lotan\u2019s sister was Timna.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 36:23"}, "These are the children of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 36:24"}, "These are the children of Zibeon: Aiah and Anah. This is Anah who found the hot springs in the wilderness, as he fed the\ndonkeys of Zibeon his father. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 36:25"}, "These are the children of Anah: Dishon and Oholibamah, the daughter of Anah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 36:26"}, "These are the children of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 36:27"}, "These are the children of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 36:28"}, "These are the children of Dishan: Uz and Aran. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 36:29"}, "These are the chiefs who came of the Horites: chief Lotan, chief Shobal, chief Zibeon, chief Anah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 36:30"}, "chief Dishon, chief Ezer, and chief Dishan. These are the chiefs who came of the Horites, according to their chiefs in\nthe land of Seir. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 36:31"}, "These are the kings who reigned in the land of Edom, before any king reigned over the children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 36:32"}, "Bela, the son of Beor, reigned in Edom. The name of his city was Dinhabah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 36:33"}, "Bela died, and Jobab, the son of Zerah of Bozrah, reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 36:34"}, "Jobab died, and Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 36:35"}, "Husham died, and Hadad, the son of Bedad, who struck Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his place. The name of his\ncity was Avith. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 36:36"}, "Hadad died, and Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 36:37"}, "Samlah died, and Shaul of Rehoboth by the river, reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 36:38"}, "Shaul died, and Baal Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 36:39"}, "Baal Hanan the son of Achbor died, and Hadar reigned in his place. The name of his city was Pau. His wife\u2019s name was\nMehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 36:40"}, "These are the names of the chiefs who came from Esau, according to their families, after their places, and by their\nnames: chief Timna, chief Alvah, chief Jetheth, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 36:41"}, "chief Oholibamah, chief Elah, chief Pinon, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 36:42"}, "chief Kenaz, chief Teman, chief Mibzar, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 36:43"}, "chief Magdiel, and chief Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom, according to their habitations in the land of their\npossession. This is Esau, the father of the Edomites. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 37"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 37:1"}, "Yaqub lived in the land of his father\u2019s travels, in the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 37:2"}, "This is the history of the generations of Yaqub. Yusuf, being seventeen years old, was feeding the flock with his\nbrothers. He was a boy with the sons of Bilhah and Zilpah, his father\u2019s wives. Yusuf brought an evil report of them to their\nfather. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 37:3"}, "Now Israel loved Yusuf more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age, and he made him a tunic of many\ncolours. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 37:4"}, "His brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his brothers, and they hated him, and couldn\u2019t speak peaceably\nto him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 37:5"}, "Yusuf dreamt a dream, and he told it to his brothers, and they hated him all the more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 37:6"}, "He said to them, \u201cPlease hear this dream which I have dreamt:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 37:7"}, "for behold, we were binding sheaves in the field, and behold, my sheaf arose and also stood upright; and behold, your\nsheaves came around, and bowed down to my sheaf.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 37:8"}, "His brothers asked him, \u201cWill you indeed reign over us? Will you indeed have dominion over us?\u201d They hated him all the\nmore for his dreams and for his words. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 37:9"}, "He dreamt yet another dream, and told it to his brothers, and said, \u201cBehold, I have dreamt yet another dream: and behold,\nthe sun and the moon and eleven stars bowed down to me.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 37:10"}, "He told it to his father and to his brothers. His father rebuked him, and said to him, \u201cWhat is this dream that you have\ndreamt? Will I and your mother and your brothers indeed come to bow ourselves down to you to the earth?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 37:11"}, "His brothers envied him, but his father kept this saying in mind.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 37:12"}, "His brothers went to feed their father\u2019s flock in Shechem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 37:13"}, "Israel said to Yusuf, \u201cAren\u2019t your brothers feeding the flock in Shechem? Come, and I will send you to them.\u201d He said to\nhim, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 37:14"}, "He said to him, \u201cGo now, see whether it is well with your brothers, and well with the flock; and bring me word again.\u201d So\nhe sent him out of the valley of Hebron, and he came to Shechem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 37:15"}, "A certain man found him, and behold, he was wandering in the field. The man asked him, \u201cWhat are you looking for?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 37:16"}, "He said, \u201cI am looking for my brothers. Tell me, please, where they are feeding the flock.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 37:17"}, "The man said, \u201cThey have left here, for I heard them say, \u2018Let\u2019s go to Dothan.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yusuf went after his brothers, and found them in Dothan. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 37:18"}, "They saw him afar off, and before he came near to them, they conspired against him to kill him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 37:19"}, "They said to one another, \u201cBehold, this dreamer comes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 37:20"}, "Come now therefore, and let\u2019s kill him, and cast him into one of the pits, and we will say, \u2018An evil animal has devoured\nhim.\u2019 We will see what will become of his dreams.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 37:21"}, "Reuben heard it, and delivered him out of their hand, and said, \u201cLet\u2019s not take his life.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 37:22"}, "Reuben said to them, \u201cShed no blood. Throw him into this pit that is in the wilderness, but lay no hand on him\u201d\u2014that he\nmight deliver him out of their hand, to restore him to his father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 37:23"}, "When Yusuf came to his brothers, they stripped Yusuf of his tunic, the tunic of many colours that was on him;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 37:24"}, "and they took him, and threw him into the pit. The pit was empty. There was no water in it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 37:25"}, "They sat down to eat bread, and they lifted up their eyes and looked, and saw a caravan of Ishmaelites was coming from\nGilead, with their camels bearing spices and balm and myrrh, going to carry it down to Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 37:26"}, "Judah said to his brothers, \u201cWhat profit is it if we kill our brother and conceal his blood?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 37:27"}, "Come, and let\u2019s sell him to the Ishmaelites, and not let our hand be on him; for he is our brother, our flesh.\u201d His\nbrothers listened to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 37:28"}, "Midianites who were merchants passed by, and they drew and lifted up Yusuf out of the pit, and sold Yusuf to the\nIshmaelites for twenty pieces of silver. The merchants brought Yusuf into Egypt.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 37:29"}, "Reuben returned to the pit, and saw that Yusuf wasn\u2019t in the pit; and he tore his clothes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 37:30"}, "He returned to his brothers, and said, \u201cThe child is no more; and I, where will I go?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 37:31"}, "They took Yusuf\u2019s tunic, and killed a male goat, and dipped the tunic in the blood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 37:32"}, "They took the tunic of many colours, and they brought it to their father, and said, \u201cWe have found this. Examine it, now,\nand see if it is your son\u2019s tunic or not.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 37:33"}, "He recognised it, and said, \u201cIt is my son\u2019s tunic. An evil animal has devoured him. Yusuf is without doubt torn in\npieces.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 37:34"}, "Yaqub tore his clothes, and put sackcloth on his waist, and mourned for his son many days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 37:35"}, "All his sons and all his daughters rose up to comfort him, but he refused to be comforted. He said, \u201cFor I will go down\nto Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["37:35 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " to my son, mourning.\u201d His father wept for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 37:36"}, "The Midianites sold him into Egypt to Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh\u2019s, the captain of the guard.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 38"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 38:1"}, "At that time, Judah went down from his brothers, and visited a certain Adullamite, whose name was Hirah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 38:2"}, "There, Judah saw the daughter of a certain Canaanite man named Shua. He took her, and went in to her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 38:3"}, "She conceived, and bore a son; and he named him Er. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 38:4"}, "She conceived again, and bore a son; and she named him Onan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 38:5"}, "She yet again bore a son, and named him Shelah. He was at Chezib when she bore him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 38:6"}, "Judah took a wife for Er, his firstborn, and her name was Tamar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 38:7"}, "Er, Judah\u2019s firstborn, was wicked in the LORD\u2019s sight. So The LORD killed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 38:8"}, "Judah said to Onan, \u201cGo in to your brother\u2019s wife, and perform the duty of a husband\u2019s brother to her, and raise up\noffspring for your brother.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 38:9"}, "Onan knew that the offspring wouldn\u2019t be his; and when he went in to his brother\u2019s wife, he spilled his semen on the\nground, lest he should give offspring to his brother. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 38:10"}, "The thing which he did was evil in the LORD\u2019s sight, and he killed him also.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 38:11"}, "Then Judah said to Tamar, his daughter-in-law, \u201cRemain a widow in your father\u2019s house, until Shelah, my son, is grown\nup;\u201d for he said, \u201cLest he also die, like his brothers.\u201d Tamar went and lived in her father\u2019s house.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 38:12"}, "After many days, Shua\u2019s daughter, the wife of Judah, died. Judah was comforted, and went up to his sheep shearers to\nTimnah, he and his friend Hirah, the Adullamite. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 38:13"}, "Tamar was told, \u201cBehold, your father-in-law is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 38:14"}, "She took off the garments of her widowhood, and covered herself with her veil, and wrapped herself, and sat in the gate\nof Enaim, which is on the way to Timnah; for she saw that Shelah was grown up, and she wasn\u2019t given to him as a wife.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 38:15"}, "When Judah saw her, he thought that she was a prostitute, for she had covered her face.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 38:16"}, "He turned to her by the way, and said, \u201cPlease come, let me come in to you,\u201d for he didn\u2019t know that she was his\ndaughter-in-law. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cWhat will you give me, that you may come in to me?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 38:17"}, "He said, \u201cI will send you a young goat from the flock.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cWill you give me a pledge, until you send it?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 38:18"}, "He said, \u201cWhat pledge will I give you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cYour signet and your cord, and your staff that is in your hand.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He gave them to her, and came in to her, and she conceived by him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 38:19"}, "She arose, and went away, and put off her veil from her, and put on the garments of her widowhood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 38:20"}, "Judah sent the young goat by the hand of his friend, the Adullamite, to receive the pledge from the woman\u2019s hand, but he\ndidn\u2019t find her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 38:21"}, "Then he asked the men of her place, saying, \u201cWhere is the prostitute, that was at Enaim by the road?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cThere has been no prostitute here.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 38:22"}, "He returned to Judah, and said, \u201cI haven\u2019t found her; and also the men of the place said, \u2018There has been no prostitute\nhere.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 38:23"}, "Judah said, \u201cLet her keep it, lest we be shamed. Behold, I sent this young goat, and you haven\u2019t found her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 38:24"}, "About three months later, Judah was told, \u201cTamar, your daughter-in-law, has played the prostitute. Moreover, behold, she\nis with child by prostitution.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Judah said, \u201cBring her out, and let her be burnt.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 38:25"}, "When she was brought out, she sent to her father-in-law, saying, \u201cI am with child by the man who owns these.\u201d She also\nsaid, \u201cPlease discern whose these are\u2014the signet, and the cords, and the staff.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 38:26"}, "Judah acknowledged them, and said, \u201cShe is more righteous than I, because I didn\u2019t give her to Shelah, my son.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He knew her again no more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 38:27"}, "In the time of her travail, behold, twins were in her womb.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 38:28"}, "When she travailed, one put out a hand, and the midwife took and tied a scarlet thread on his hand, saying, \u201cThis came\nout first.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 38:29"}, "As he drew back his hand, behold, his brother came out, and she said, \u201cWhy have you made a breach for yourself?\u201d\nTherefore his name was called Perez.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["38:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Perez means \u201cbreaking\nout\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 38:30"}, "Afterward his brother came out, who had the scarlet thread on his hand, and his name was called\nZerah.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["38:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Zerah means \u201cscarlet\u201d or \u201cbrightness\u201d.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 39"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 39:1"}, "Yusuf was brought down to Egypt. Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh\u2019s, the captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him from\nthe hand of the Ishmaelites that had brought him down there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 39:2"}, "The LORD was with Yusuf, and he was a prosperous man. He was in the house of his master the Egyptian.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 39:3"}, "His master saw that the LORD was with him, and that the LORD made all that he did prosper in his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 39:4"}, "Yusuf found favour in his sight. He ministered to him, and Potiphar made him overseer over his house, and all that he had\nhe put into his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 39:5"}, "From the time that he made him overseer in his house, and over all that he had, the LORD blessed the Egyptian\u2019s house for\nYusuf\u2019s sake. The LORD\u2019s blessing was on all that he had, in the house and in the field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 39:6"}, "He left all that he had in Yusuf\u2019s hand. He didn\u2019t concern himself with anything, except for the food which he ate.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yusuf was well-built and handsome. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 39:7"}, "After these things, his master\u2019s wife set her eyes on Yusuf; and she said, \u201cLie with me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 39:8"}, "But he refused, and said to his master\u2019s wife, \u201cBehold, my master doesn\u2019t know what is with me in the house, and he has\nput all that he has into my hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 39:9"}, "No one is greater in this house than I am, and he has not kept back anything from me but you, because you are his wife.\nHow then can I do this great wickedness, and sin against Allah?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 39:10"}, "As she spoke to Yusuf day by day, he didn\u2019t listen to her, to lie by her, or to be with her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 39:11"}, "About this time, he went into the house to do his work, and there were none of the men of the house inside.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 39:12"}, "She caught him by his garment, saying, \u201cLie with me!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He left his garment in her hand, and ran outside. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 39:13"}, "When she saw that he had left his garment in her hand, and had run outside,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 39:14"}, "she called to the men of her house, and spoke to them, saying, \u201cBehold, he has brought a Hebrew in to us to mock us. He\ncame in to me to lie with me, and I cried with a loud voice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 39:15"}, "When he heard that I lifted up my voice and cried, he left his garment by me, and ran outside.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 39:16"}, "She laid up his garment by her, until his master came home.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 39:17"}, "She spoke to him according to these words, saying, \u201cThe Hebrew servant, whom you have brought to us, came in to me to\nmock me, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 39:18"}, "and as I lifted up my voice and cried, he left his garment by me, and ran outside.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 39:19"}, "When his master heard the words of his wife, which she spoke to him, saying, \u201cThis is what your servant did to me,\u201d his\nwrath was kindled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 39:20"}, "Yusuf\u2019s master took him, and put him into the prison, the place where the king\u2019s prisoners were bound, and he was there\nin custody. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 39:21"}, "But the LORD was with Yusuf, and showed kindness to him, and gave him favour in the sight of the keeper of the prison.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 39:22"}, "The keeper of the prison committed to Yusuf\u2019s hand all the prisoners who were in the prison. Whatever they did there, he\nwas responsible for it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 39:23"}, "The keeper of the prison didn\u2019t look after anything that was under his hand, because the LORD was with him; and that\nwhich he did, the LORD made it prosper. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 40"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 40:1"}, "After these things, the butler of the king of Egypt and his baker offended their lord, the king of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 40:2"}, "Pharaoh was angry with his two officers, the chief cup bearer and the chief baker.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 40:3"}, "He put them in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, into the prison, the place where Yusuf was bound.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 40:4"}, "The captain of the guard assigned them to Yusuf, and he took care of them. They stayed in prison many days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 40:5"}, "They both dreamt a dream, each man his dream, in one night, each man according to the interpretation of his dream, the cup\nbearer and the baker of the king of Egypt, who were bound in the prison.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 40:6"}, "Yusuf came in to them in the morning, and saw them, and saw that they were sad.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 40:7"}, "He asked Pharaoh\u2019s officers who were with him in custody in his master\u2019s house, saying, \u201cWhy do you look so sad today?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 40:8"}, "They said to him, \u201cWe have dreamt a dream, and there is no one who can interpret it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yusuf said to them, \u201cDon\u2019t interpretations belong to Allah? Please tell it to me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 40:9"}, "The chief cup bearer told his dream to Yusuf, and said to him, \u201cIn my dream, behold, a vine was in front of me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 40:10"}, "and in the vine were three branches. It was as though it budded, it blossomed, and its clusters produced ripe grapes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 40:11"}, "Pharaoh\u2019s cup was in my hand; and I took the grapes, and pressed them into Pharaoh\u2019s cup, and I gave the cup into\nPharaoh\u2019s hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 40:12"}, "Yusuf said to him, \u201cThis is its interpretation: the three branches are three days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 40:13"}, "Within three more days, Pharaoh will lift up your head, and restore you to your office. You will give Pharaoh\u2019s cup into\nhis hand, the way you did when you were his cup bearer. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 40:14"}, "But remember me when it is well with you. Please show kindness to me, and make mention of me to Pharaoh, and bring me out\nof this house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 40:15"}, "For indeed, I was stolen away out of the land of the Hebrews, and here also I have done nothing that they should put me\ninto the dungeon.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 40:16"}, "When the chief baker saw that the interpretation was good, he said to Yusuf, \u201cI also was in my dream, and behold, three\nbaskets of white bread were on my head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 40:17"}, "In the uppermost basket there were all kinds of baked food for Pharaoh, and the birds ate them out of the basket on my\nhead.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 40:18"}, "Yusuf answered, \u201cThis is its interpretation. The three baskets are three days.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 40:19"}, "Within three more days, Pharaoh will lift up your head from off you, and will hang you on a tree; and the birds will eat\nyour flesh from off you.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 40:20"}, "On the third day, which was Pharaoh\u2019s birthday, he made a feast for all his servants, and he lifted up the head of the\nchief cup bearer and the head of the chief baker amongst his servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 40:21"}, "He restored the chief cup bearer to his position again, and he gave the cup into Pharaoh\u2019s hand;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 40:22"}, "but he hanged the chief baker, as Yusuf had interpreted to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 40:23"}, "Yet the chief cup bearer didn\u2019t remember Yusuf, but forgot him.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 41"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 41:1"}, "At the end of two full years, Pharaoh dreamt, and behold, he stood by the river.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 41:2"}, "Behold, seven cattle came up out of the river. They were sleek and fat, and they fed in the marsh grass.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 41:3"}, "Behold, seven other cattle came up after them out of the river, ugly and thin, and stood by the other cattle on the brink\nof the river. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 41:4"}, "The ugly and thin cattle ate up the seven sleek and fat cattle. So Pharaoh awoke.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 41:5"}, "He slept and dreamt a second time; and behold, seven heads of grain came up on one stalk, healthy and good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 41:6"}, "Behold, seven heads of grain, thin and blasted with the east wind, sprung up after them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 41:7"}, "The thin heads of grain swallowed up the seven healthy and full ears. Pharaoh awoke, and behold, it was a dream.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 41:8"}, "In the morning, his spirit was troubled, and he sent and called for all of Egypt\u2019s magicians and wise men. Pharaoh told\nthem his dreams, but there was no one who could interpret them to Pharaoh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 41:9"}, "Then the chief cup bearer spoke to Pharaoh, saying, \u201cI remember my faults today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 41:10"}, "Pharaoh was angry with his servants, and put me in custody in the house of the captain of the guard, with the chief\nbaker. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 41:11"}, "We dreamt a dream in one night, he and I. Each man dreamt according to the interpretation of his dream.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 41:12"}, "There was with us there a young man, a Hebrew, servant to the captain of the guard, and we told him, and he interpreted\nto us our dreams. He interpreted to each man according to his dream.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 41:13"}, "As he interpreted to us, so it was. He restored me to my office, and he hanged him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 41:14"}, "Then Pharaoh sent and called Yusuf, and they brought him hastily out of the dungeon. He shaved himself, changed his\nclothing, and came in to Pharaoh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 41:15"}, "Pharaoh said to Yusuf, \u201cI have dreamt a dream, and there is no one who can interpret it. I have heard it said of you,\nthat when you hear a dream you can interpret it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 41:16"}, "Yusuf answered Pharaoh, saying, \u201cIt isn\u2019t in me. Allah will give Pharaoh an answer of peace.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 41:17"}, "Pharaoh spoke to Yusuf, \u201cIn my dream, behold, I stood on the brink of the river;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 41:18"}, "and behold, there came up out of the river seven cattle, fat and sleek. They fed in the marsh grass;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 41:19"}, "and behold, seven other cattle came up after them, poor and very ugly and thin, such as I never saw in all the land of\nEgypt for ugliness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 41:20"}, "The thin and ugly cattle ate up the first seven fat cattle;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 41:21"}, "and when they had eaten them up, it couldn\u2019t be known that they had eaten them, but they were still ugly, as at the\nbeginning. So I awoke. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 41:22"}, "I saw in my dream, and behold, seven heads of grain came up on one stalk, full and good;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 41:23"}, "and behold, seven heads of grain, withered, thin, and blasted with the east wind, sprung up after them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 41:24"}, "The thin heads of grain swallowed up the seven good heads of grain. I told it to the magicians, but there was no one who\ncould explain it to me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 41:25"}, "Yusuf said to Pharaoh, \u201cThe dream of Pharaoh is one. What Allah is about to do he has declared to Pharaoh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 41:26"}, "The seven good cattle are seven years; and the seven good heads of grain are seven years. The dream is one.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 41:27"}, "The seven thin and ugly cattle that came up after them are seven years, and also the seven empty heads of grain blasted\nwith the east wind; they will be seven years of famine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 41:28"}, "That is the thing which I have spoken to Pharaoh. Allah has shown Pharaoh what he is about to do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 41:29"}, "Behold, seven years of great plenty throughout all the land of Egypt are coming.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 41:30"}, "Seven years of famine will arise after them, and all the plenty will be forgotten in the land of Egypt. The famine will\nconsume the land, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 41:31"}, "and the plenty will not be known in the land by reason of that famine which follows; for it will be very grievous.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 41:32"}, "The dream was doubled to Pharaoh, because the thing is established by Allah, and Allah will shortly bring it to pass.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 41:33"}, "\u201cNow therefore let Pharaoh look for a discreet and wise man, and set him over the land of Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 41:34"}, "Let Pharaoh do this, and let him appoint overseers over the land, and take up the fifth part of the land of Egypt\u2019s\nproduce in the seven plenteous years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 41:35"}, "Let them gather all the food of these good years that come, and store grain under the hand of Pharaoh for food in the\ncities, and let them keep it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 41:36"}, "The food will be to supply the land against the seven years of famine, which will be in the land of Egypt; so that the\nland will not perish through the famine.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 41:37"}, "The thing was good in the eyes of Pharaoh, and in the eyes of all his servants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 41:38"}, "Pharaoh said to his servants, \u201cCan we find such a one as this, a man in whom is the Spirit of Allah?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "GEN 41:39"}, "Pharaoh said to Yusuf, \u201cBecause Allah has shown you all of this, there is no one so discreet and wise as you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "GEN 41:40"}, "You shall be over my house. All my people will be ruled according to your word. Only in the throne I will be greater than\nyou.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "GEN 41:41"}, "Pharaoh said to Yusuf, \u201cBehold, I have set you over all the land of Egypt.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 41:42"}, "Pharaoh took off his signet ring from his hand, and put it on Yusuf\u2019s hand, and arrayed him in robes of fine linen, and\nput a gold chain about his neck. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 41:43"}, "He made him ride in the second chariot which he had. They cried before him, \u201cBow the knee!\u201d He set him over all the land\nof Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "GEN 41:44"}, "Pharaoh said to Yusuf, \u201cI am Pharaoh. Without you, no man shall lift up his hand or his foot in all the land of Egypt.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "GEN 41:45"}, "Pharaoh called Yusuf\u2019s name Zaphenath-Paneah. He gave him Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On as a wife.\nYusuf went out over the land of Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "GEN 41:46"}, "Yusuf was thirty years old when he stood before Pharaoh king of Egypt. Yusuf went out from the presence of Pharaoh, and\nwent throughout all the land of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "GEN 41:47"}, "In the seven plenteous years the earth produced abundantly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "GEN 41:48"}, "He gathered up all the food of the seven years which were in the land of Egypt, and laid up the food in the cities. He\nstored food in each city from the fields around that city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "GEN 41:49"}, "Yusuf laid up grain as the sand of the sea, very much, until he stopped counting, for it was without number.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "GEN 41:50"}, "To Yusuf were born two sons before the year of famine came, whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera priest of On, bore to\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "GEN 41:51"}, "Yusuf called the name of the firstborn Manasseh,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["41:51\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cManasseh\u201d sounds like the Hebrew for \u201cforget\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \u201cFor\u201d, he said, \u201cAllah has made me forget all my toil, and all my\nfather\u2019s house.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "GEN 41:52"}, "The name of the second, he called Ephraim:", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["41:52 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cEphraim\u201d sounds like the Hebrew for \u201ctwice\nfruitful\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \u201cFor Allah has made me fruitful in the land of my affliction.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "GEN 41:53"}, "The seven years of plenty, that were in the land of Egypt, came to an end.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "GEN 41:54"}, "The seven years of famine began to come, just as Yusuf had said. There was famine in all lands, but in all the land of\nEgypt there was bread. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "GEN 41:55"}, "When all the land of Egypt was famished, the people cried to Pharaoh for bread, and Pharaoh said to all the Egyptians,\n\u201cGo to Yusuf. What he says to you, do.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "GEN 41:56"}, "The famine was over all the surface of the earth. Yusuf opened all the store houses, and sold to the Egyptians. The\nfamine was severe in the land of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "GEN 41:57"}, "All countries came into Egypt, to Yusuf, to buy grain, because the famine was severe in all the earth.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "42", "sid": "GEN 42"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 42:1"}, "Now Yaqub saw that there was grain in Egypt, and Yaqub said to his sons, \u201cWhy do you look at one another?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 42:2"}, "He said, \u201cBehold, I have heard that there is grain in Egypt. Go down there, and buy for us from there, so that we may\nlive, and not die.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 42:3"}, "Yusuf\u2019s ten brothers went down to buy grain from Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 42:4"}, "But Yaqub didn\u2019t send Benjamin, Yusuf\u2019s brother, with his brothers; for he said, \u201cLest perhaps harm happen to him.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 42:5"}, "The sons of Israel came to buy amongst those who came, for the famine was in the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 42:6"}, "Yusuf was the governor over the land. It was he who sold to all the people of the land. Yusuf\u2019s brothers came, and bowed\nthemselves down to him with their faces to the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 42:7"}, "Yusuf saw his brothers, and he recognised them, but acted like a stranger to them, and spoke roughly with them. He said to\nthem, \u201cWhere did you come from?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cFrom the land of Canaan, to buy food.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 42:8"}, "Yusuf recognised his brothers, but they didn\u2019t recognise him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 42:9"}, "Yusuf remembered the dreams which he dreamt about them, and said to them, \u201cYou are spies! You have come to see the\nnakedness of the land.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 42:10"}, "They said to him, \u201cNo, my lord, but your servants have come to buy food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 42:11"}, "We are all one man\u2019s sons; we are honest men. Your servants are not spies.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 42:12"}, "He said to them, \u201cNo, but you have come to see the nakedness of the land!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 42:13"}, "They said, \u201cWe, your servants, are twelve brothers, the sons of one man in the land of Canaan; and behold, the youngest\nis today with our father, and one is no more.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 42:14"}, "Yusuf said to them, \u201cIt is like I told you, saying, \u2018You are spies!\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 42:15"}, "By this you shall be tested. By the life of Pharaoh, you shall not go out from here, unless your youngest brother comes\nhere. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 42:16"}, "Send one of you, and let him get your brother, and you shall be bound, that your words may be tested, whether there is\ntruth in you, or else by the life of Pharaoh surely you are spies.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 42:17"}, "He put them all together into custody for three days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 42:18"}, "Yusuf said to them the third day, \u201cDo this, and live, for I fear Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 42:19"}, "If you are honest men, then let one of your brothers be bound in your prison; but you go, carry grain for the famine of\nyour houses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 42:20"}, "Bring your youngest brother to me; so will your words be verified, and you won\u2019t die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They did so. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 42:21"}, "They said to one another, \u201cWe are certainly guilty concerning our brother, in that we saw the distress of his soul, when\nhe begged us, and we wouldn\u2019t listen. Therefore this distress has come upon us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 42:22"}, "Reuben answered them, saying, \u201cDidn\u2019t I tell you, saying, \u2018Don\u2019t sin against the child,\u2019 and you wouldn\u2019t listen?\nTherefore also, behold, his blood is required.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 42:23"}, "They didn\u2019t know that Yusuf understood them; for there was an interpreter between them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 42:24"}, "He turned himself away from them, and wept. Then he returned to them, and spoke to them, and took Simeon from amongst\nthem, and bound him before their eyes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 42:25"}, "Then Yusuf gave a command to fill their bags with grain, and to restore each man\u2019s money into his sack, and to give them\nfood for the way. So it was done to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 42:26"}, "They loaded their donkeys with their grain, and departed from there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 42:27"}, "As one of them opened his sack to give his donkey food in the lodging place, he saw his money. Behold, it was in the\nmouth of his sack. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 42:28"}, "He said to his brothers, \u201cMy money is restored! Behold, it is in my sack!\u201d Their hearts failed them, and they turned\ntrembling to one another, saying, \u201cWhat is this that Allah has done to us?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 42:29"}, "They came to Yaqub their father, to the land of Canaan, and told him all that had happened to them, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 42:30"}, "\u201cThe man, the lord of the land, spoke roughly with us, and took us for spies of the country.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 42:31"}, "We said to him, \u2018We are honest men. We are no spies. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 42:32"}, "We are twelve brothers, sons of our father; one is no more, and the youngest is today with our father in the land of\nCanaan.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 42:33"}, "The man, the lord of the land, said to us, \u2018By this I will know that you are honest men: leave one of your brothers with\nme, and take grain for the famine of your houses, and go your way.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 42:34"}, "Bring your youngest brother to me. Then I will know that you are not spies, but that you are honest men. So I will\ndeliver your brother to you, and you shall trade in the land.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "GEN 42:35"}, "As they emptied their sacks, behold, each man\u2019s bundle of money was in his sack. When they and their father saw their\nbundles of money, they were afraid. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "GEN 42:36"}, "Yaqub, their father, said to them, \u201cYou have bereaved me of my children! Yusuf is no more, Simeon is no more, and you\nwant to take Benjamin away. All these things are against me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "GEN 42:37"}, "Reuben spoke to his father, saying, \u201cKill my two sons, if I don\u2019t bring him to you. Entrust him to my care, and I will\nbring him to you again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "GEN 42:38"}, "He said, \u201cMy son shall not go down with you; for his brother is dead, and he only is left. If harm happens to him along\nthe way in which you go, then you will bring down my grey hairs with sorrow to\nSheol.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["42:38 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "43", "sid": "GEN 43"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 43:1"}, "The famine was severe in the land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 43:2"}, "When they had eaten up the grain which they had brought out of Egypt, their father said to them, \u201cGo again, buy us a\nlittle more food.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 43:3"}, "Judah spoke to him, saying, \u201cThe man solemnly warned us, saying, \u2018You shall not see my face, unless your brother is with\nyou.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 43:4"}, "If you\u2019ll send our brother with us, we\u2019ll go down and buy you food;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 43:5"}, "but if you don\u2019t send him, we won\u2019t go down, for the man said to us, \u2018You shall not see my face, unless your brother is\nwith you.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 43:6"}, "Israel said, \u201cWhy did you treat me so badly, telling the man that you had another brother?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 43:7"}, "They said, \u201cThe man asked directly concerning ourselves, and concerning our relatives, saying, \u2018Is your father still\nalive? Have you another brother?\u2019 We just answered his questions. Is there any way we could know that he would say, \u2018Bring your\nbrother down?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 43:8"}, "Judah said to Israel, his father, \u201cSend the boy with me, and we\u2019ll get up and go, so that we may live, and not die, both\nwe, and you, and also our little ones. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 43:9"}, "I\u2019ll be collateral for him. From my hand will you require him. If I don\u2019t bring him to you, and set him before you, then\nlet me bear the blame forever; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 43:10"}, "for if we hadn\u2019t delayed, surely we would have returned a second time by now.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 43:11"}, "Their father, Israel, said to them, \u201cIf it must be so, then do this: Take from the choice fruits of the land in your\nbags, and carry down a present for the man, a little balm, a little honey, spices and myrrh, nuts, and almonds;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 43:12"}, "and take double money in your hand, and take back the money that was returned in the mouth of your sacks. Perhaps it was\nan oversight. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 43:13"}, "Take your brother also, get up, and return to the man. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 43:14"}, "May Allah Ta\u2019ala give you mercy before the man, that he may release to you your other brother and Benjamin. If I am\nbereaved of my children, I am bereaved.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 43:15"}, "The men took that present, and they took double money in their hand, and Benjamin; and got up, went down to Egypt, and\nstood before Yusuf. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 43:16"}, "When Yusuf saw Benjamin with them, he said to the steward of his house, \u201cBring the men into the house, and butcher an\nanimal, and prepare; for the men will dine with me at noon.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 43:17"}, "The man did as Yusuf commanded, and the man brought the men to Yusuf\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 43:18"}, "The men were afraid, because they were brought to Yusuf\u2019s house; and they said, \u201cBecause of the money that was returned\nin our sacks the first time, we\u2019re brought in; that he may seek occasion against us, attack us, and seize us as slaves, along\nwith our donkeys.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 43:19"}, "They came near to the steward of Yusuf\u2019s house, and they spoke to him at the door of the house,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 43:20"}, "and said, \u201cOh, my lord, we indeed came down the first time to buy food.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 43:21"}, "When we came to the lodging place, we opened our sacks, and behold, each man\u2019s money was in the mouth of his sack, our\nmoney in full weight. We have brought it back in our hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 43:22"}, "We have brought down other money in our hand to buy food. We don\u2019t know who put our money in our sacks.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 43:23"}, "He said, \u201cPeace be to you. Don\u2019t be afraid. Your Allah, and Allah of your father, has given you treasure in your sacks. I\nreceived your money.\u201d He brought Simeon out to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 43:24"}, "The man brought the men into Yusuf\u2019s house, and gave them water, and they washed their feet. He gave their donkeys\nfodder. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 43:25"}, "They prepared the present for Yusuf\u2019s coming at noon, for they heard that they should eat bread there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 43:26"}, "When Yusuf came home, they brought him the present which was in their hand into the house, and bowed themselves down to\nthe earth before him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 43:27"}, "He asked them of their welfare, and said, \u201cIs your father well, the old man of whom you spoke? Is he yet alive?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 43:28"}, "They said, \u201cYour servant, our father, is well. He is still alive.\u201d They bowed down humbly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 43:29"}, "He lifted up his eyes, and saw Benjamin, his brother, his mother\u2019s son, and said, \u201cIs this your youngest brother, of whom\nyou spoke to me?\u201d He said, \u201cAllah be gracious to you, my son.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 43:30"}, "Yusuf hurried, for his heart yearned over his brother; and he sought a place to weep. He entered into his room, and wept\nthere. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 43:31"}, "He washed his face, and came out. He controlled himself, and said, \u201cServe the meal.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 43:32"}, "They served him by himself, and them by themselves, and the Egyptians who ate with him by themselves, because the\nEgyptians don\u2019t eat with the Hebrews, for that is an abomination to the Egyptians.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 43:33"}, "They sat before him, the firstborn according to his birthright, and the youngest according to his youth, and the men\nmarvelled with one another. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 43:34"}, "He sent portions to them from before him, but Benjamin\u2019s portion was five times as much as any of theirs. They drank, and\nwere merry with him. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "44", "sid": "GEN 44"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 44:1"}, "He commanded the steward of his house, saying, \u201cFill the men\u2019s sacks with food, as much as they can carry, and put each\nman\u2019s money in his sack\u2019s mouth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 44:2"}, "Put my cup, the silver cup, in the sack\u2019s mouth of the youngest, with his grain money.\u201d He did according to the word that\nYusuf had spoken. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 44:3"}, "As soon as the morning was light, the men were sent away, they and their donkeys.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 44:4"}, "When they had gone out of the city, and were not yet far off, Yusuf said to his steward, \u201cUp, follow after the men. When\nyou overtake them, ask them, \u2018Why have you rewarded evil for good?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 44:5"}, "Isn\u2019t this that from which my lord drinks, and by which he indeed divines? You have done evil in so doing.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 44:6"}, "He overtook them, and he spoke these words to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 44:7"}, "They said to him, \u201cWhy does my lord speak such words as these? Far be it from your servants that they should do such a\nthing! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 44:8"}, "Behold, the money, which we found in our sacks\u2019 mouths, we brought again to you out of the land of Canaan. How then should\nwe steal silver or gold out of your lord\u2019s house? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 44:9"}, "With whomever of your servants it is found, let him die, and we also will be my lord\u2019s slaves.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 44:10"}, "He said, \u201cNow also let it be according to your words. He with whom it is found will be my slave; and you will be\nblameless.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 44:11"}, "Then they hurried, and each man took his sack down to the ground, and each man opened his sack.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 44:12"}, "He searched, beginning with the oldest, and ending at the youngest. The cup was found in Benjamin\u2019s sack.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 44:13"}, "Then they tore their clothes, and each man loaded his donkey, and returned to the city.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 44:14"}, "Judah and his brothers came to Yusuf\u2019s house, and he was still there. They fell on the ground before him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 44:15"}, "Yusuf said to them, \u201cWhat deed is this that you have done? Don\u2019t you know that such a man as I can indeed do divination?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 44:16"}, "Judah said, \u201cWhat will we tell my lord? What will we speak? How will we clear ourselves? Allah has found out the iniquity\nof your servants. Behold, we are my lord\u2019s slaves, both we and he also in whose hand the cup is found.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 44:17"}, "He said, \u201cFar be it from me that I should do so. The man in whose hand the cup is found, he will be my slave; but as for\nyou, go up in peace to your father.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 44:18"}, "Then Judah came near to him, and said, \u201cOh, my lord, please let your servant speak a word in my lord\u2019s ears, and don\u2019t\nlet your anger burn against your servant; for you are even as Pharaoh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 44:19"}, "My lord asked his servants, saying, \u2018Have you a father, or a brother?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 44:20"}, "We said to my lord, \u2018We have a father, an old man, and a child of his old age, a little one; and his brother is dead, and\nhe alone is left of his mother; and his father loves him.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 44:21"}, "You said to your servants, \u2018Bring him down to me, that I may set my eyes on him.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 44:22"}, "We said to my lord, \u2018The boy can\u2019t leave his father, for if he should leave his father, his father would die.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 44:23"}, "You said to your servants, \u2018Unless your youngest brother comes down with you, you will see my face no more.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 44:24"}, "When we came up to your servant my father, we told him the words of my lord.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 44:25"}, "Our father said, \u2018Go again and buy us a little food.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 44:26"}, "We said, \u2018We can\u2019t go down. If our youngest brother is with us, then we will go down: for we may not see the man\u2019s face,\nunless our youngest brother is with us.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 44:27"}, "Your servant, my father, said to us, \u2018You know that my wife bore me two sons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 44:28"}, "One went out from me, and I said, \u201cSurely he is torn in pieces;\u201d and I haven\u2019t seen him since.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 44:29"}, "If you take this one also from me, and harm happens to him, you will bring down my grey hairs with sorrow to\nSheol.\u2019", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["44:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 44:30"}, "Now therefore when I come to your servant my father, and the boy is not with us; since his life is bound up in the boy\u2019s\nlife; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 44:31"}, "it will happen, when he sees that the boy is no more, that he will die. Your servants will bring down the grey hairs of\nyour servant, our father, with sorrow to Sheol.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["44:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 44:32"}, "For your servant became collateral for the boy to my father, saying, \u2018If I don\u2019t bring him to you, then I will bear the\nblame to my father forever.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 44:33"}, "Now therefore, please let your servant stay instead of the boy, my lord\u2019s slave; and let the boy go up with his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 44:34"}, "For how will I go up to my father, if the boy isn\u2019t with me?\u2014lest I see the evil that will come on my father.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "45", "sid": "GEN 45"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 45:1"}, "Then Yusuf couldn\u2019t control himself before all those who stood before him, and he called out, \u201cCause everyone to go out\nfrom me!\u201d No one else stood with him, while Yusuf made himself known to his brothers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 45:2"}, "He wept aloud. The Egyptians heard, and the house of Pharaoh heard.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 45:3"}, "Yusuf said to his brothers, \u201cI am Yusuf! Does my father still live?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["His brothers couldn\u2019t answer him; for they were terrified at his presence.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 45:4"}, "Yusuf said to his brothers, \u201cCome near to me, please.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They came near. He said, \u201cI am Yusuf, your brother, whom you sold into Egypt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 45:5"}, "Now don\u2019t be grieved, nor angry with yourselves, that you sold me here, for Allah sent me before you to preserve life.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 45:6"}, "For these two years the famine has been in the land, and there are yet five years, in which there will be no ploughing and\nno harvest. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 45:7"}, "Allah sent me before you to preserve for you a remnant in the earth, and to save you alive by a great deliverance.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 45:8"}, "So now it wasn\u2019t you who sent me here, but Allah, and he has made me a father to Pharaoh, lord of all his house, and ruler\nover all the land of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 45:9"}, "Hurry, and go up to my father, and tell him, \u2018This is what your son Yusuf says, \u201cAllah has made me lord of all Egypt. Come\ndown to me. Don\u2019t wait. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 45:10"}, "You shall dwell in the land of Goshen, and you will be near to me, you, your children, your children\u2019s children, your\nflocks, your herds, and all that you have. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 45:11"}, "There I will provide for you; for there are yet five years of famine; lest you come to poverty, you, and your household,\nand all that you have.\u201d\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 45:12"}, "Behold, your eyes see, and the eyes of my brother Benjamin, that it is my mouth that speaks to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 45:13"}, "You shall tell my father of all my glory in Egypt, and of all that you have seen. You shall hurry and bring my father\ndown here.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 45:14"}, "He fell on his brother Benjamin\u2019s neck and wept, and Benjamin wept on his neck.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 45:15"}, "He kissed all his brothers, and wept on them. After that his brothers talked with him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 45:16"}, "The report of it was heard in Pharaoh\u2019s house, saying, \u201cYusuf\u2019s brothers have come.\u201d It pleased Pharaoh well, and his\nservants. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 45:17"}, "Pharaoh said to Yusuf, \u201cTell your brothers, \u2018Do this: Load your animals, and go, travel to the land of Canaan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 45:18"}, "Take your father and your households, and come to me, and I will give you the good of the land of Egypt, and you will eat\nthe fat of the land.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 45:19"}, "Now you are commanded to do this: Take wagons out of the land of Egypt for your little ones, and for your wives, and\nbring your father, and come. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 45:20"}, "Also, don\u2019t concern yourselves about your belongings, for the good of all the land of Egypt is yours.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 45:21"}, "The sons of Israel did so. Yusuf gave them wagons, according to the commandment of Pharaoh, and gave them provision for\nthe way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 45:22"}, "He gave each one of them changes of clothing, but to Benjamin he gave three hundred pieces of silver and five changes of\nclothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 45:23"}, "He sent the following to his father: ten donkeys loaded with the good things of Egypt, and ten female donkeys loaded with\ngrain and bread and provision for his father by the way. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 45:24"}, "So he sent his brothers away, and they departed. He said to them, \u201cSee that you don\u2019t quarrel on the way.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 45:25"}, "They went up out of Egypt, and came into the land of Canaan, to Yaqub their father.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 45:26"}, "They told him, saying, \u201cYusuf is still alive, and he is ruler over all the land of Egypt.\u201d His heart fainted, for he\ndidn\u2019t believe them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 45:27"}, "They told him all the words of Yusuf, which he had said to them. When he saw the wagons which Yusuf had sent to carry\nhim, the spirit of Yaqub, their father, revived. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 45:28"}, "Israel said, \u201cIt is enough. Yusuf my son is still alive. I will go and see him before I die.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "46", "sid": "GEN 46"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 46:1"}, "Israel travelled with all that he had, and came to Beersheba, and offered sacrifices to Allah of his father, Is\u1e25\u0101q.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 46:2"}, "Allah spoke to Israel in the visions of the night, and said, \u201cYaqub, Yaqub!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cHere I am.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 46:3"}, "He said, \u201cI am Allah, Allah of your father. Don\u2019t be afraid to go down into Egypt, for there I will make of you a great\nnation. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 46:4"}, "I will go down with you into Egypt. I will also surely bring you up again. Yusuf\u2019s hand will close your eyes.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 46:5"}, "Yaqub rose up from Beersheba, and the sons of Israel carried Yaqub, their father, their little ones, and their wives, in\nthe wagons which Pharaoh had sent to carry him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 46:6"}, "They took their livestock, and their goods, which they had gotten in the land of Canaan, and came into Egypt\u2014Yaqub, and\nall his offspring with him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 46:7"}, "his sons, and his sons\u2019 sons with him, his daughters, and his sons\u2019 daughters, and he brought all his offspring with him\ninto Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 46:8"}, "These are the names of the children of Israel, who came into Egypt, Yaqub and his sons: Reuben, Yaqub\u2019s firstborn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 46:9"}, "The sons of Reuben: Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 46:10"}, "The sons of Simeon: Jemuel, Jamin, Ohad, Jachin, Zohar, and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 46:11"}, "The sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 46:12"}, "The sons of Judah: Er, Onan, Shelah, Perez, and Zerah; but Er and Onan died in the land of Canaan. The sons of Perez were\nHezron and Hamul. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 46:13"}, "The sons of Issachar: Tola, Puvah, Iob, and Shimron. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 46:14"}, "The sons of Zebulun: Sered, Elon, and Jahleel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 46:15"}, "These are the sons of Leah, whom she bore to Yaqub in Paddan Aram, with his daughter Dinah. All the souls of his sons and\nhis daughters were thirty-three. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 46:16"}, "The sons of Gad: Ziphion, Haggi, Shuni, Ezbon, Eri, Arodi, and Areli.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 46:17"}, "The sons of Asher: Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and Serah their sister. The sons of Beriah: Heber and Malchiel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 46:18"}, "These are the sons of Zilpah, whom Laban gave to Leah, his daughter, and these she bore to Yaqub, even sixteen souls.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 46:19"}, "The sons of Rachel, Yaqub\u2019s wife: Yusuf and Benjamin. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 46:20"}, "To Yusuf in the land of Egypt were born Manasseh and Ephraim, whom Asenath, the daughter of Potiphera, priest of On, bore\nto him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 46:21"}, "The sons of Benjamin: Bela, Becher, Ashbel, Gera, Naaman, Ehi, Rosh, Muppim, Huppim, and Ard.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 46:22"}, "These are the sons of Rachel, who were born to Yaqub: all the souls were fourteen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 46:23"}, "The son of Dan: Hushim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 46:24"}, "The sons of Naphtali: Jahzeel, Guni, Jezer, and Shillem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 46:25"}, "These are the sons of Bilhah, whom Laban gave to Rachel, his daughter, and these she bore to Yaqub: all the souls were\nseven. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 46:26"}, "All the souls who came with Yaqub into Egypt, who were his direct offspring, in addition to Yaqub\u2019s sons\u2019 wives, all the\nsouls were sixty-six. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 46:27"}, "The sons of Yusuf, who were born to him in Egypt, were two souls. All the souls of the house of Yaqub, who came into\nEgypt, were seventy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 46:28"}, "Yaqub sent Judah before him to Yusuf, to show the way before him to Goshen, and they came into the land of Goshen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 46:29"}, "Yusuf prepared his chariot, and went up to meet Israel, his father, in Goshen. He presented himself to him, and fell on\nhis neck, and wept on his neck a good while. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 46:30"}, "Israel said to Yusuf, \u201cNow let me die, since I have seen your face, that you are still alive.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 46:31"}, "Yusuf said to his brothers, and to his father\u2019s house, \u201cI will go up, and speak with Pharaoh, and will tell him, \u2018My\nbrothers, and my father\u2019s house, who were in the land of Canaan, have come to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 46:32"}, "These men are shepherds, for they have been keepers of livestock, and they have brought their flocks, and their herds,\nand all that they have.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 46:33"}, "It will happen, when Pharaoh summons you, and will say, \u2018What is your occupation?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "GEN 46:34"}, "that you shall say, \u2018Your servants have been keepers of livestock from our youth even until now, both we, and our\nfathers:\u2019 that you may dwell in the land of Goshen; for every shepherd is an abomination to the Egyptians.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "47", "sid": "GEN 47"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 47:1"}, "Then Yusuf went in and told Pharaoh, and said, \u201cMy father and my brothers, with their flocks, their herds, and all that\nthey own, have come out of the land of Canaan; and behold, they are in the land of Goshen.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 47:2"}, "From amongst his brothers he took five men, and presented them to Pharaoh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 47:3"}, "Pharaoh said to his brothers, \u201cWhat is your occupation?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to Pharaoh, \u201cYour servants are shepherds, both we, and our fathers.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 47:4"}, "They also said to Pharaoh, \u201cWe have come to live as foreigners in the land, for there is no pasture for your servants\u2019\nflocks. For the famine is severe in the land of Canaan. Now therefore, please let your servants dwell in the land of Goshen.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 47:5"}, "Pharaoh spoke to Yusuf, saying, \u201cYour father and your brothers have come to you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 47:6"}, "The land of Egypt is before you. Make your father and your brothers dwell in the best of the land. Let them dwell in the\nland of Goshen. If you know any able men amongst them, then put them in charge of my livestock.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 47:7"}, "Yusuf brought in Yaqub, his father, and set him before Pharaoh; and Yaqub blessed Pharaoh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 47:8"}, "Pharaoh said to Yaqub, \u201cHow old are you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 47:9"}, "Yaqub said to Pharaoh, \u201cThe years of my pilgrimage are one hundred and thirty years. The days of the years of my life have\nbeen few and evil. They have not attained to the days of the years of the life of my fathers in the days of their pilgrimage.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 47:10"}, "Yaqub blessed Pharaoh, and went out from the presence of Pharaoh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 47:11"}, "Yusuf placed his father and his brothers, and gave them a possession in the land of Egypt, in the best of the land, in\nthe land of Rameses, as Pharaoh had commanded. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 47:12"}, "Yusuf provided his father, his brothers, and all of his father\u2019s household with bread, according to the sizes of their\nfamilies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 47:13"}, "There was no bread in all the land; for the famine was very severe, so that the land of Egypt and the land of Canaan\nfainted by reason of the famine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 47:14"}, "Yusuf gathered up all the money that was found in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, for the grain which they\nbought: and Yusuf brought the money into Pharaoh\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 47:15"}, "When the money was all spent in the land of Egypt, and in the land of Canaan, all the Egyptians came to Yusuf, and said,\n\u201cGive us bread, for why should we die in your presence? For our money fails.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 47:16"}, "Yusuf said, \u201cGive me your livestock; and I will give you food for your livestock, if your money is gone.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 47:17"}, "They brought their livestock to Yusuf, and Yusuf gave them bread in exchange for the horses, and for the flocks, and for\nthe herds, and for the donkeys: and he fed them with bread in exchange for all their livestock for that year.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 47:18"}, "When that year was ended, they came to him the second year, and said to him, \u201cWe will not hide from my lord how our money\nis all spent, and the herds of livestock are my lord\u2019s. There is nothing left in the sight of my lord, but our bodies, and our\nlands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 47:19"}, "Why should we die before your eyes, both we and our land? Buy us and our land for bread, and we and our land will be\nservants to Pharaoh. Give us seed, that we may live, and not die, and that the land won\u2019t be desolate.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 47:20"}, "So Yusuf bought all the land of Egypt for Pharaoh, for every man of the Egyptians sold his field, because the famine was\nsevere on them, and the land became Pharaoh\u2019s. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 47:21"}, "As for the people, he moved them to the cities from one end of the border of Egypt even to the other end of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 47:22"}, "Only he didn\u2019t buy the land of the priests, for the priests had a portion from Pharaoh, and ate their portion which\nPharaoh gave them. That is why they didn\u2019t sell their land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 47:23"}, "Then Yusuf said to the people, \u201cBehold, I have bought you and your land today for Pharaoh. Behold, here is seed for you,\nand you shall sow the land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 47:24"}, "It will happen at the harvests, that you shall give a fifth to Pharaoh, and four parts will be your own, for seed of the\nfield, for your food, for them of your households, and for food for your little ones.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 47:25"}, "They said, \u201cYou have saved our lives! Let us find favour in the sight of my lord, and we will be Pharaoh\u2019s servants.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 47:26"}, "Yusuf made it a statute concerning the land of Egypt to this day, that Pharaoh should have the fifth. Only the land of\nthe priests alone didn\u2019t become Pharaoh\u2019s. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 47:27"}, "Israel lived in the land of Egypt, in the land of Goshen; and they got themselves possessions therein, and were fruitful,\nand multiplied exceedingly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 47:28"}, "Yaqub lived in the land of Egypt seventeen years. So the days of Yaqub, the years of his life, were one hundred and\nforty-seven years. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 47:29"}, "The time came near that Israel must die, and he called his son Yusuf, and said to him, \u201cIf now I have found favour in\nyour sight, please put your hand under my thigh, and deal kindly and truly with me. Please don\u2019t bury me in Egypt,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 47:30"}, "but when I sleep with my fathers, you shall carry me out of Egypt, and bury me in their burying place.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Yusuf said, \u201cI will do as you have said.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 47:31"}, "Israel said, \u201cSwear to me,\u201d and he swore to him. Then Israel bowed himself on the bed\u2019s head.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "48", "sid": "GEN 48"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 48:1"}, "After these things, someone said to Yusuf, \u201cBehold, your father is sick.\u201d He took with him his two sons, Manasseh and\nEphraim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 48:2"}, "Someone told Yaqub, and said, \u201cBehold, your son Yusuf comes to you,\u201d and Israel strengthened himself, and sat on the bed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 48:3"}, "Yaqub said to Yusuf, \u201cAllah Ta\u2019ala appeared to me at Luz in the land of Canaan, and blessed me,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 48:4"}, "and said to me, \u2018Behold, I will make you fruitful, and multiply you, and I will make of you a company of peoples, and will\ngive this land to your offspring after you for an everlasting possession.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 48:5"}, "Now your two sons, who were born to you in the land of Egypt before I came to you into Egypt, are mine; Ephraim and\nManasseh, even as Reuben and Simeon, will be mine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 48:6"}, "Your offspring, whom you become the father of after them, will be yours. They will be called after the name of their\nbrothers in their inheritance. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 48:7"}, "As for me, when I came from Paddan, Rachel died beside me in the land of Canaan on the way, when there was still some\ndistance to come to Ephrath, and I buried her there on the way to Ephrath (also called Bethlehem).\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 48:8"}, "Israel saw Yusuf\u2019s sons, and said, \u201cWho are these?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 48:9"}, "Yusuf said to his father, \u201cThey are my sons, whom Allah has given me here.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cPlease bring them to me, and I will bless them.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 48:10"}, "Now the eyes of Israel were dim for age, so that he couldn\u2019t see well. Yusuf brought them near to him; and he kissed\nthem, and embraced them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 48:11"}, "Israel said to Yusuf, \u201cI didn\u2019t think I would see your face, and behold, Allah has let me see your offspring also.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 48:12"}, "Yusuf brought them out from between his knees, and he bowed himself with his face to the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 48:13"}, "Yusuf took them both, Ephraim in his right hand towards Israel\u2019s left hand, and Manasseh in his left hand towards\nIsrael\u2019s right hand, and brought them near to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 48:14"}, "Israel stretched out his right hand, and laid it on Ephraim\u2019s head, who was the younger, and his left hand on Manasseh\u2019s\nhead, guiding his hands knowingly, for Manasseh was the firstborn.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 48:15"}, "He blessed Yusuf, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThe Allah before whom my fathers Ibrahim and Is\u1e25\u0101q walked, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Allah who has fed me all my life long to this day, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 48:16"}, "the angel who has redeemed me from all evil, bless the lads,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and let my name be named on them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and the name of my fathers Ibrahim and Is\u1e25\u0101q. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them grow into a multitude upon the earth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 48:17"}, "When Yusuf saw that his father laid his right hand on the head of Ephraim, it displeased him. He held up his father\u2019s\nhand, to remove it from Ephraim\u2019s head to Manasseh\u2019s head. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 48:18"}, "Yusuf said to his father, \u201cNot so, my father, for this is the firstborn. Put your right hand on his head.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 48:19"}, "His father refused, and said, \u201cI know, my son, I know. He also will become a people, and he also will be great. However,\nhis younger brother will be greater than he, and his offspring will become a multitude of nations.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 48:20"}, "He blessed them that day, saying, \u201cIsrael will bless in you, saying, \u2018Allah make you as Ephraim and as Manasseh\u2019\u201d He set\nEphraim before Manasseh. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 48:21"}, "Israel said to Yusuf, \u201cBehold, I am dying, but Allah will be with you, and bring you again to the land of your fathers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 48:22"}, "Moreover I have given to you one portion above your brothers, which I took out of the hand of the Amorite with my sword\nand with my bow.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "49", "sid": "GEN 49"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 49:1"}, "Yaqub called to his sons, and said: \u201cGather yourselves together, that I may tell you that which will happen to you in the\ndays to come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 49:2"}, "Assemble yourselves, and hear, you sons of Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Listen to Israel, your father. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 49:3"}, "\u201cReuben, you are my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my strength;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["excelling in dignity, and excelling in power. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 49:4"}, "Boiling over like water, you shall not excel; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because you went up to your father\u2019s bed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["then defiled it. He went up to my couch. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 49:5"}, "\u201cSimeon and Levi are brothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their swords are weapons of violence. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 49:6"}, "My soul, don\u2019t come into their council. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My glory, don\u2019t be united to their assembly; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for in their anger they killed men. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["In their self-will they hamstrung cattle. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 49:7"}, "Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their wrath, for it was cruel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will divide them in Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and scatter them in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 49:8"}, "\u201cJudah, your brothers will praise you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your hand will be on the neck of your enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your father\u2019s sons will bow down before you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 49:9"}, "Judah is a lion\u2019s cub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From the prey, my son, you have gone up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He stooped down, he crouched as a lion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a lioness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who will rouse him up? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 49:10"}, "The sceptre will not depart from Judah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor the ruler\u2019s staff from between his feet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["until he comes to whom it belongs. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["To him will the obedience of the peoples be. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 49:11"}, "Binding his foal to the vine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["his donkey\u2019s colt to the choice vine; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["he has washed his garments in wine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["his robes in the blood of grapes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 49:12"}, "His eyes will be red with wine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["his teeth white with milk. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 49:13"}, "\u201cZebulun will dwell at the haven of the sea. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will be for a haven of ships. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His border will be on Sidon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 49:14"}, "\u201cIssachar is a strong donkey, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lying down between the saddlebags. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 49:15"}, "He saw a resting place, that it was good, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the land, that it was pleasant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He bows his shoulder to the burden, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and becomes a servant doing forced labour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 49:16"}, "\u201cDan will judge his people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as one of the tribes of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 49:17"}, "Dan will be a serpent on the trail, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["an adder in the path, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["That bites the horse\u2019s heels, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that his rider falls backward. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 49:18"}, "I have waited for your salvation, LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 49:19"}, "\u201cA troop will press on Gad, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but he will press on their heel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 49:20"}, "\u201cAsher\u2019s food will be rich. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will produce royal dainties. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 49:21"}, "\u201cNaphtali is a doe set free, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who bears beautiful fawns. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 49:22"}, "\u201cYusuf is a fruitful vine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a fruitful vine by a spring. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His branches run over the wall. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 49:23"}, "The archers have severely grieved him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["shot at him, and persecuted him: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 49:24"}, "But his bow remained strong. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The arms of his hands were made strong, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["by the hands of the Mighty One of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["(from there is the shepherd, the stone of Israel), \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 49:25"}, "even by Allah of your father, who will help you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["by the Almighty, who will bless you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["with blessings of heaven above, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["blessings of the deep that lies below, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["blessings of the breasts, and of the womb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 49:26"}, "The blessings of your father have prevailed above the blessings of your ancestors,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["above the boundaries of the ancient hills. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will be on the head of Yusuf, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["on the crown of the head of him who is separated from his brothers.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "GEN 49:27"}, "\u201cBenjamin is a ravenous wolf. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["In the morning he will devour the prey. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["At evening he will divide the plunder.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "GEN 49:28"}, "All these are the twelve tribes of Israel, and this is what their father spoke to them, and blessed them. He blessed\neveryone according to his own blessing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "GEN 49:29"}, "He instructed them, and said to them, \u201cI am to be gathered to my people. Bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in\nthe field of Ephron the Hittite, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "GEN 49:30"}, "in the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan, which Ibrahim bought with\nthe field from Ephron the Hittite as a burial place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "GEN 49:31"}, "There they buried Ibrahim and Sarah, his wife. There they buried Is\u1e25\u0101q and Rebekah, his wife, and there I buried Leah:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "GEN 49:32"}, "the field and the cave that is therein, which was purchased from the children of Heth.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "GEN 49:33"}, "When Yaqub finished charging his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, breathed his last breath, and was gathered\nto his people. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "50", "sid": "GEN 50"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "nb", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "GEN 50:1"}, "Yusuf fell on his father\u2019s face, wept on him, and kissed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "GEN 50:2"}, "Yusuf commanded his servants, the physicians, to embalm his father; and the physicians embalmed Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "GEN 50:3"}, "Forty days were used for him, for that is how many the days it takes to embalm. The Egyptians wept for Israel for seventy\ndays. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "GEN 50:4"}, "When the days of weeping for him were past, Yusuf spoke to Pharaoh\u2019s staff, saying, \u201cIf now I have found favour in your\neyes, please speak in the ears of Pharaoh, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "GEN 50:5"}, "\u2018My father made me swear, saying, \u201cBehold, I am dying. Bury me in my grave which I have dug for myself in the land of\nCanaan.\u201d Now therefore, please let me go up and bury my father, and I will come again.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "GEN 50:6"}, "Pharaoh said, \u201cGo up, and bury your father, just like he made you swear.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "GEN 50:7"}, "Yusuf went up to bury his father; and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his house, all the\nelders of the land of Egypt, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "GEN 50:8"}, "All the house of Yusuf, his brothers, and his father\u2019s house. Only their little ones, their flocks, and their herds, they\nleft in the land of Goshen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "GEN 50:9"}, "There went up with him both chariots and horsemen. It was a very great company.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "GEN 50:10"}, "They came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond the Jordan, and there they lamented with a very great and\nsevere lamentation. He mourned for his father seven days. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "GEN 50:11"}, "When the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning in the floor of Atad, they said, \u201cThis is a grievous\nmourning by the Egyptians.\u201d Therefore its name was called Habil Mizraim, which is beyond the Jordan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "GEN 50:12"}, "His sons did to him just as he commanded them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "GEN 50:13"}, "for his sons carried him into the land of Canaan, and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah, which Ibrahim\nbought with the field, as a possession for a burial site, from Ephron the Hittite, near Mamre.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "GEN 50:14"}, "Yusuf returned into Egypt\u2014he, and his brothers, and all that went up with him to bury his father, after he had buried his\nfather. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "GEN 50:15"}, "When Yusuf\u2019s brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, \u201cIt may be that Yusuf will hate us, and will fully pay\nus back for all the evil which we did to him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "GEN 50:16"}, "They sent a message to Yusuf, saying, \u201cYour father commanded before he died, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "GEN 50:17"}, "\u2018You shall tell Yusuf, \u201cNow please forgive the disobedience of your brothers, and their sin, because they did evil to\nyou.\u201d\u2019 Now, please forgive the disobedience of the servants of Allah of your father.\u201d Yusuf wept when they spoke to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "GEN 50:18"}, "His brothers also went and fell down before his face; and they said, \u201cBehold, we are your servants.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "GEN 50:19"}, "Yusuf said to them, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, for am I in the place of Allah?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "GEN 50:20"}, "As for you, you meant evil against me, but Allah meant it for good, to save many people alive, as is happening today.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "GEN 50:21"}, "Now therefore don\u2019t be afraid. I will provide for you and your little ones.\u201d He comforted them, and spoke kindly to them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "GEN 50:22"}, "Yusuf lived in Egypt, he, and his father\u2019s house. Yusuf lived one hundred and ten years.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "GEN 50:23"}, "Yusuf saw Ephraim\u2019s children to the third generation. The children also of Machir, the son of Manasseh, were born on\nYusuf\u2019s knees. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "GEN 50:24"}, "Yusuf said to his brothers, \u201cI am dying, but Allah will surely visit you, and bring you up out of this land to the land\nwhich he swore to Ibrahim, to Is\u1e25\u0101q, and to Yaqub.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "GEN 50:25"}, "Yusuf took an oath from the children of Israel, saying, \u201cAllah will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones\nfrom here.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "GEN 50:26"}, "So Yusuf died, being one hundred and ten years old, and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.\n"]}]}